77 
78 ChordRest* Score::getSelectedChordRest() const
79  {
80  Element* el = selection().element();
81  if (el) {
82  if (el->isNote())
83  return toNote(el)->chord();
84  else if (el->isRest() || el->isRepeatMeasure())
85  return toRest(el);
86  else if (el->isChord())
87  return toChord(el);
88  }
89  MScore::setError(NO_NOTE_REST_SELECTED);
90  return 0;
91  }

93 //---------------------------------------------------------
94 // getSelectedChordRest2
95 //---------------------------------------------------------
96 
97 void Score::getSelectedChordRest2(ChordRest** cr1, ChordRest** cr2) const
98  {
99  *cr1 = 0;
100  *cr2 = 0;
101  for (Element* e : selection().elements()) {
102  if (e->isNote())
103  e = e->parent();
104  if (e->isChordRest()) {
105  ChordRest* cr = toChordRest(e);
106  if (*cr1 == 0 || (*cr1)->tick() > cr->tick())
107  *cr1 = cr;
108  if (*cr2 == 0 || (*cr2)->tick() < cr->tick())
109  *cr2 = cr;
110  }
111  }
112  if (*cr1 == 0)
113  MScore::setError(NO_NOTE_REST_SELECTED);
114  if (*cr1 == *cr2)
115  *cr2 = 0;
116  }

135 //---------------------------------------------------------
136 // pos
137 //---------------------------------------------------------
138 
139 Fraction Score::pos()
140  {
141  Element* el = selection().element();
142  if (selection().activeCR())
143  el = selection().activeCR();
144  if (el) {
145  switch (el->type()) {
146  case ElementType::NOTE:
147  el = el->parent();
148  // fall through
149  case ElementType::REPEAT_MEASURE:
150  case ElementType::REST:
151  case ElementType::CHORD:
152  return toChordRest(el)->tick();
153  default:
154  break;
155  }
156  }
157  return Fraction(-1, 1);
158  }

166 Rest* Score::addRest(const Fraction& tick, int track, TDuration d, Tuplet* tuplet)
167  {
168  Measure* measure = tick2measure(tick);
169  Rest* rest = new Rest(this, d);
170  if (d.type() == TDuration::DurationType::V_MEASURE)
171  rest->setTicks(measure->stretchedLen(staff(track/VOICES)));
172  else
173  rest->setTicks(d.fraction());
174  rest->setTrack(track);
175  rest->setTuplet(tuplet);
176  undoAddCR(rest, measure, tick);
177  return rest;
178  }

198 //---------------------------------------------------------
199 // addChord
200 // Create one Chord at tick with duration d
201 // - create segment if necessary.
202 // - Use chord "oc" as prototype;
203 // - if "genTie" then tie to chord "oc"
204 //---------------------------------------------------------
205 
206 Chord* Score::addChord(const Fraction& tick, TDuration d, Chord* oc, bool genTie, Tuplet* tuplet)
207  {
208  Measure* measure = tick2measure(tick);
209  if (measure->endTick() <= tick) {
210  qDebug("Score::addChord(): end of score?");
211  return 0;
212  }
213 
214  Chord* chord = new Chord(this);
215  chord->setTuplet(tuplet);
216  chord->setTrack(oc->track());
217  chord->setDurationType(d);
218  chord->setTicks(d.fraction());
219 
220  for (Note* n : oc->notes()) {
221  Note* nn = new Note(this);
222  nn->setPitch(n->pitch());
223  nn->setTpc1(n->tpc1());
224  nn->setTpc2(n->tpc2());
225  chord->add(nn);
226  }
227  undoAddCR(chord, measure, tick);
228 
229  //
230  // now as both chords are in place
231  // (have segments as parent) we can add ties:
232  //
233  if (genTie) {
234  size_t n = oc->notes().size();
235  for(size_t i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
236  Note* n1 = oc->notes()[i];
237  Note* n2 = chord->notes()[i];
238  Tie* tie = new Tie(this);
239  tie->setStartNote(n1);
240  tie->setEndNote(n2);
241  tie->setTick(tie->startNote()->tick());
242  tie->setTick2(tie->endNote()->tick());
243  tie->setTrack(n1->track());
244  undoAddElement(tie);
245  }
246  }
247 
248  return chord;
249  }

255 ChordRest* Score::addClone(ChordRest* cr, const Fraction& tick, const TDuration& d)
256  {
257  ChordRest* newcr;
258  // change a RepeatMeasure() into an Rest()
259  if (cr->isRepeatMeasure())
260  newcr = new Rest(*toRest(cr));
261  else
262  newcr = toChordRest(cr->clone());
263  newcr->rxpos() = 0.0;
264  newcr->setDurationType(d);
265  newcr->setTicks(d.fraction());
266  newcr->setTuplet(cr->tuplet());
267  newcr->setSelected(false);
268 
269  undoAddCR(newcr, cr->measure(), tick);
270  return newcr;
271  }

273 //---------------------------------------------------------
274 // setRest
275 // create one or more rests to fill "l"
276 //---------------------------------------------------------
277 
278 Rest* Score::setRest(const Fraction& _tick, int track, const Fraction& _l, bool useDots, Tuplet* tuplet, bool useFullMeasureRest)
279  {
280  Fraction l = _l;
281  Fraction tick = _tick;
282  Measure* measure = tick2measure(tick);
283  Rest* r = 0;
284  Staff* staff = Score::staff(track / VOICES);
285 
286  while (!l.isZero()) {
287  //
288  // divide into measures
289  //
290  Fraction f;
291  if (tuplet) {
292  f = tuplet->baseLen().fraction() * tuplet->ratio().numerator();
293  for (DurationElement* de : tuplet->elements()) {
294  if (de->tick() >= tick)
295  break;
296  f -= de->ticks();
297  }
298  //
299  // restrict to tuplet len
300  //
301  if (f < l)
302  l = f;
303  }
304  else {
305  if (measure->tick() < tick)
306  f = measure->tick() + measure->ticks() - tick;
307  else
308  f = measure->ticks();
309  f *= staff->timeStretch(tick);
310  }
311 
312  if (f > l)
313  f = l;
314 
315  if ((track % VOICES) && !measure->hasVoice(track) && (tick == measure->tick())) {
316  l -= f;
317  measure = measure->nextMeasure();
318  if (!measure)
319  break;
320  tick = measure->tick();
321  continue;
322  }
323 
324  if ((measure->timesig() == measure->ticks()) // not in pickup measure
325  && (measure->tick() == tick)
326  && (measure->stretchedLen(staff) == f)
327  && !tuplet
328  && (useFullMeasureRest)) {
329  Rest* rest = addRest(tick, track, TDuration(TDuration::DurationType::V_MEASURE), tuplet);
330  tick += rest->actualTicks();
331  if (r == 0)
332  r = rest;
333  }
334  else {
335  //
336  // compute list of durations which will fit l
337  //
338  std::vector<TDuration> dList;
339  if (tuplet || staff->isLocalTimeSignature(tick)) {
340  dList = toDurationList(l, useDots);
341  std::reverse(dList.begin(), dList.end());
342  }
343  else {
344  dList = toRhythmicDurationList(f, true, tick - measure->tick(), sigmap()->timesig(tick).nominal(), measure, useDots ? 1 : 0);
345  }
346  if (dList.empty())
347  return 0;
348 
349  Rest* rest = 0;
350  for (const TDuration& d : dList) {
351  rest = addRest(tick, track, d, tuplet);
352  if (r == 0)
353  r = rest;
354  tick += rest->actualTicks();
355  }
356  }
357  l -= f;
358 
359  measure = measure->nextMeasure();
360  if (!measure)
361  break;
362  tick = measure->tick();
363  }
364  return r;
365  }

371 Note* Score::addNote(Chord* chord, const NoteVal& noteVal, bool forceAccidental, InputState* externalInputState)
372  {
373  InputState& is = externalInputState ? (*externalInputState) : _is;
374 
375  Note* note = new Note(this);
376  note->setParent(chord);
377  note->setTrack(chord->track());
378  note->setNval(noteVal);
379  undoAddElement(note);
380  if (forceAccidental) {
381  int tpc = styleB(Sid::concertPitch) ? noteVal.tpc1 : noteVal.tpc2;
382  AccidentalVal alter = tpc2alter(tpc);
383  AccidentalType at = Accidental::value2subtype(alter);
384  Accidental* a = new Accidental(this);
385  a->setAccidentalType(at);
386  a->setRole(AccidentalRole::USER);
387  a->setParent(note);
388  undoAddElement(a);
389  }
390  setPlayNote(true);
391  setPlayChord(true);
392 
393  if (externalInputState) {
394  is.setTrack(note->track());
395  is.setLastSegment(is.segment());
396  is.setSegment(note->chord()->segment());
397  }
398  else {
399  select(note, SelectType::SINGLE, 0);
400  }
401 
402  if (!chord->staff()->isTabStaff(chord->tick())) {
403  NoteEntryMethod entryMethod = is.noteEntryMethod();
404  if (entryMethod != NoteEntryMethod::REALTIME_AUTO && entryMethod != NoteEntryMethod::REALTIME_MANUAL)
405  is.moveToNextInputPos();
406  }
407  return note;
408  }

410 //---------------------------------------------------------
411 // rewriteMeasures
412 // rewrite all measures from fm to lm (including)
413 // If staffIdx is valid (>= 0), then rewrite a local
414 // timesig change.
415 //---------------------------------------------------------
416 
417 bool Score::rewriteMeasures(Measure* fm, Measure* lm, const Fraction& ns, int staffIdx)
418  {
419  if (staffIdx >= 0) {
420  // local timesig
421  // don't actually rewrite, just update measure rest durations
422  // abort if there is anything other than measure rests in range
423  int strack = staffIdx * VOICES;
424  int etrack = strack + VOICES;
425  for (Measure* m = fm; ; m = m->nextMeasure()) {
426  for (Segment* s = m->first(SegmentType::ChordRest); s; s = s->next(SegmentType::ChordRest)) {
427  for (int track = strack; track < etrack; ++track) {
428  ChordRest* cr = toChordRest(s->element(track));
429  if (!cr)
430  continue;
431  if (cr->isRest() && cr->durationType() == TDuration::DurationType::V_MEASURE)
432  cr->undoChangeProperty(Pid::DURATION, QVariant::fromValue(ns));
433  else
434  return false;
435  }
436  }
437  if (m == lm)
438  break;
439  }
440  return true;
441  }
442  int measures = 1;
443  bool fmr = true;
444 
445  // Format: chord 1 tick, chord 2 tick, tremolo, track
446  std::vector<std::tuple<Fraction, Fraction, Tremolo*, int>> tremoloChordTicks;
447 
448  int strack, etrack;
449  if (staffIdx < 0) {
450  strack = 0;
451  etrack = ntracks();
452  }
453  else {
454  strack = staffIdx * VOICES;
455  etrack = strack + VOICES;
456  }
457 
458  for (Measure* m = fm; m; m = m->nextMeasure()) {
459  if (!m->isFullMeasureRest())
460  fmr = false;
461 
462  for (Segment* s = m->first(SegmentType::ChordRest); s; s = s->next(SegmentType::ChordRest)) {
463  for (int track = strack; track < etrack; ++track) {
464  ChordRest* cr = toChordRest(s->element(track));
465  if (cr && cr->isChord()) {
466  Chord* chord = toChord(cr);
467  if (chord->tremolo() && chord->tremolo()->twoNotes()) {
468  Tremolo* trem = chord->tremolo();
469 
470  // Don't add same chord twice
471  if (trem->chord2() == chord)
472  continue;
473  auto newP = std::tuple<Fraction, Fraction, Tremolo*, int>(cr->tick(), trem->chord2()->segment()->tick(), trem, track);
474  tremoloChordTicks.push_back(newP);
475  }
476  }
477  }
478  }
479 
480  if (m == lm)
481  break;
482  ++measures;
483  }
484 
485  if (!fmr) {
486  // check for local time signatures
487  for (Measure* m = fm; m; m = m -> nextMeasure()) {
488  for (int si = 0; si < nstaves(); ++si) {
489  if (staff(si)->timeStretch(m->tick()) != Fraction(1,1)) {
490  // we cannot change a staff with a local time signature
491  return false;
492  }
493  if (m == lm)
494  break;
495  }
496  }
497  }
498 
499  ScoreRange range;
500  range.read(fm->first(), lm->last());
501 
502  //
503  // calculate number of required measures = nm
504  //
505  Fraction k = range.ticks() / ns;
506  int nm = (k.numerator() + k.denominator() - 1)/ k.denominator();
507 
508  Fraction nd = ns * Fraction(nm,1);
509 
510  // evtl. we have to fill the last measure
511  Fraction fill = nd - range.ticks();
512  range.fill(fill);
513 
514  for (Score* s : scoreList()) {
515  Measure* m1 = s->tick2measure(fm->tick());
516  Measure* m2 = s->tick2measure(lm->tick());
517 
518  Fraction tick1 = m1->tick();
519  Fraction tick2 = m2->endTick();
520  auto spanners = s->spannerMap().findOverlapping(tick1.ticks(), tick2.ticks());
521  for (auto i : spanners) {
522  if (i.value->tick() >= tick1 && i.value->tick() < tick2)
523  undo(new RemoveElement(i.value));
524  }
525  s->undoRemoveMeasures(m1, m2, true);
526 
527  Measure* nfm = 0;
528  Measure* nlm = 0;
529  Fraction tick = { 0, 1};
530  for (int i = 0; i < nm; ++i) {
531  Measure* m = new Measure(s);
532  m->setPrev(nlm);
533  if (nlm)
534  nlm->setNext(m);
535  m->setTimesig(ns);
536  m->setTicks(ns);
537  m->setTick(tick);
538  tick += m->ticks();
539  nlm = m;
540  if (nfm == 0)
541  nfm = m;
542  }
543 // nlm->setEndBarLineType(m2->endBarLineType(), m2->endBarLineGenerated(),
544 // m2->endBarLineVisible(), m2->endBarLineColor());
545  //
546  // insert new calculated measures
547  //
548  nfm->setPrev(m1->prev());
549  nlm->setNext(m2->next());
550  s->undo(new InsertMeasures(nfm, nlm));
551  }
552  if (!fill.isZero())
553  undoInsertTime(lm->endTick(), fill);
554 
555  if (!range.write(masterScore(), fm->tick()))
556  return false;
557  connectTies(true);
558 
559  // Attempt to move tremolos to correct chords
560  for (auto tremPair : tremoloChordTicks) {
561  Fraction chord1Tick = std::get<0>(tremPair);
562  Fraction chord2Tick = std::get<1>(tremPair);
563  Tremolo* trem = std::get<2>(tremPair);
564  int track = std::get<3>(tremPair);
565 
566  undo(new MoveTremolo(trem->score(), chord1Tick, chord2Tick, trem, track));
567  }
568 
569  if (noteEntryMode()) {
570  // set input cursor to possibly re-written segment
571  Fraction icTick = inputPos();
572  Segment* icSegment = tick2segment(icTick, false, SegmentType::ChordRest);
573  if (!icSegment) {
574  // this can happen if cursor was on a rest
575  // and in the rewriting it got subsumed into a full measure rest
576  Measure* icMeasure = tick2measure(icTick);
577  if (!icMeasure) // shouldn't happen, but just in case
578  icMeasure = firstMeasure();
579  icSegment = icMeasure->first(SegmentType::ChordRest);
580  }
581  inputState().setSegment(icSegment);
582  }
583 
584  return true;
585  }

587 //---------------------------------------------------------
588 // rewriteMeasures
589 // rewrite all measures up to the next time signature or section break
590 //---------------------------------------------------------
591 
592 bool Score::rewriteMeasures(Measure* fm, const Fraction& ns, int staffIdx)
593  {
594  Measure* lm = fm;
595  Measure* fm1 = fm;
596  Measure* nm = nullptr;
597  LayoutBreak* sectionBreak = nullptr;
598 
599  // disable local time sig modifications in linked staves
600  if (staffIdx != -1 && excerpts().size() > 0) {
601  MScore::setError(CANNOT_CHANGE_LOCAL_TIMESIG);
602  return false;
603  }
604 
605  //
606  // split into Measure segments fm-lm
607  //
608  for (MeasureBase* measure = fm; ; measure = measure->next()) {
609 
610  if (!measure || !measure->isMeasure() || lm->sectionBreak()
611  || (toMeasure(measure)->first(SegmentType::TimeSig) && measure != fm))
612  {
613 
614  // save section break to reinstate after rewrite
615  if (lm->sectionBreak())
616  sectionBreak = new LayoutBreak(*lm->sectionBreakElement());
617 
618  if (!rewriteMeasures(fm1, lm, ns, staffIdx)) {
619  if (staffIdx >= 0) {
620  MScore::setError(CANNOT_CHANGE_LOCAL_TIMESIG);
621  // restore measure rests that were prematurely modified
622  Fraction fr(staff(staffIdx)->timeSig(fm->tick())->sig());
623  for (Measure* m = fm1; m; m = m->nextMeasure()) {
624  ChordRest* cr = m->findChordRest(m->tick(), staffIdx * VOICES);
625  if (cr && cr->isRest() && cr->durationType() == TDuration::DurationType::V_MEASURE)
626  cr->undoChangeProperty(Pid::DURATION, QVariant::fromValue(fr));
627  else
628  break;
629  }
630  }
631  for (Measure* m = fm1; m; m = m->nextMeasure()) {
632  if (m->first(SegmentType::TimeSig))
633  break;
634  Fraction fr(ns);
635  m->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG_NOMINAL, QVariant::fromValue(fr));
636  }
637  return false;
638  }
639 
640  // after rewrite, lm is not necessarily valid
641  // m is first MeasureBase after rewritten range
642  // m->prevMeasure () is new last measure of range
643  // set nm to first true Measure after rewritten range
644  // we may use this to reinstate time signatures
645  if (measure && measure->prevMeasure())
646  nm = measure->prevMeasure()->nextMeasure();
647  else
648  nm = nullptr;
649 
650  if (sectionBreak) {
651  // reinstate section break, then stop rewriting
652  if (measure && measure->prevMeasure()) {
653  sectionBreak->setParent(measure->prevMeasure());
654  undoAddElement(sectionBreak);
655  }
656  else if (!measure) {
657  sectionBreak->setParent(lastMeasure());
658  undoAddElement(sectionBreak);
659  }
660  else {
661  qDebug("unable to restore section break");
662  nm = nullptr;
663  sectionBreak = nullptr;
664  }
665  break;
666  }
667 
668  // stop rewriting at end of score
669  // or at a measure (which means we found a time signature segment)
670  if (!measure || measure->isMeasure())
671  break;
672 
673  // skip frames
674  while (!measure->isMeasure()) {
675  if (measure->sectionBreak()) {
676  // frame has a section break; we can stop skipping ahead
677  sectionBreak = measure->sectionBreakElement();
678  break;
679  }
680  measure = measure->next();
681  if (!measure)
682  break;
683  }
684  // stop rewriting if we encountered a section break on a frame
685  // or if there is a time signature on first measure after the frame
686  if (sectionBreak || (measure && toMeasure(measure)->first(SegmentType::TimeSig)))
687  break;
688 
689  // set up for next range to rewrite
690  fm1 = toMeasure(measure);
691  if (fm1 == 0)
692  break;
693  }
694 
695  // if we didn't break the loop already,
696  // we must have an ordinary measure
697  // add measure to range to rewrite
698  lm = toMeasure(measure);
699  }
700 
701  // if any staves don't have time signatures at the point where we stopped,
702  // we need to reinstate their previous time signatures
703  if (!nm)
704  return true;
705  Segment* s = nm->undoGetSegment(SegmentType::TimeSig, nm->tick());
706  for (int i = 0; i < nstaves(); ++i) {
707  if (!s->element(i * VOICES)) {
708  TimeSig* ots = staff(i)->timeSig(nm->tick());
709  if (ots) {
710  TimeSig* nts = new TimeSig(*ots);
711  nts->setParent(s);
712  if (sectionBreak) {
713  nts->setGenerated(false);
714  nts->setShowCourtesySig(false);
715  }
716  undoAddElement(nts);
717  }
718  }
719  }
720 
721  return true;
722  }

724 //---------------------------------------------------------
725 // cmdAddTimeSig
726 //
727 // Add or change time signature at measure in response
728 // to gui command (drop timesig on measure or timesig)
729 //---------------------------------------------------------
730 
731 void Score::cmdAddTimeSig(Measure* fm, int staffIdx, TimeSig* ts, bool local)
732  {
733  deselectAll();
734 
735  if (fm->isMMRest())
736  fm = fm->mmRestFirst();
737 
738  Fraction ns = ts->sig();
739  Fraction tick = fm->tick();
740  TimeSig* lts = staff(staffIdx)->timeSig(tick);
741  if (local) {
742  Fraction stretch = (ns / fm->timesig()).reduced();
743  ts->setStretch(stretch);
744  }
745 
746  Fraction stretch;
747  Fraction lsig; // last signature
748  if (lts) {
749  stretch = lts->stretch();
750  lsig = lts->sig();
751  }
752  else {
753  stretch.set(1,1);
754  lsig.set(4,4); // set to default
755  }
756 
757  int track = staffIdx * VOICES;
758  Segment* seg = fm->undoGetSegment(SegmentType::TimeSig, tick);
759  TimeSig* ots = toTimeSig(seg->element(track));
760 
761  if (ots && (*ots == *ts)) {
762  //
763  // ignore if there is already a timesig
764  // with same values
765  //
766  delete ts;
767  return;
768  }
769 
770  auto getStaffIdxRange = [this, local, staffIdx](const Score* score) -> std::pair<int /*start*/, int /*end*/> {
771  int startStaffIdx, endStaffIdx;
772  if (local) {
773  if (score == this) {
774  startStaffIdx = staffIdx;
775  endStaffIdx = startStaffIdx + 1;
776  }
777  else {
778  // TODO: get index for this score
779  qDebug("cmdAddTimeSig: unable to write local time signature change to linked score");
780  startStaffIdx = 0;
781  endStaffIdx = 0;
782  }
783  }
784  else {
785  startStaffIdx = 0;
786  endStaffIdx = score->nstaves();
787  }
788  return std::make_pair(startStaffIdx, endStaffIdx);
789  };
790 
791  if (ots && ots->sig() == ns && ots->stretch() == ts->stretch()) {
792  //
793  // the measure duration does not change,
794  // so its ok to just update the time signatures
795  //
796  TimeSig* nts = staff(staffIdx)->nextTimeSig(tick + Fraction::fromTicks(1));
797  const Fraction lmTick = nts ? nts->segment()->tick() : Fraction(-1, 1);
798  for (Score* score : scoreList()) {
799  Measure* mf = score->tick2measure(tick);
800  Measure* lm = (lmTick != Fraction(-1, 1)) ? score->tick2measure(lmTick) : nullptr;
801  for (Measure* m = mf; m != lm; m = m->nextMeasure()) {
802  bool changeActual = m->ticks() == m->timesig();
803  m->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG_NOMINAL, QVariant::fromValue(ns));
804  if (changeActual)
805  m->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG_ACTUAL, QVariant::fromValue(ns));
806  }
807  std::pair<int, int> staffIdxRange = getStaffIdxRange(score);
808  for (int si = staffIdxRange.first; si < staffIdxRange.second; ++si) {
809  TimeSig* nsig = toTimeSig(seg->element(si * VOICES));
810  if (!nsig)
811  continue;
812  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SHOW_COURTESY, ts->showCourtesySig());
813  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG, QVariant::fromValue(ts->sig()));
814  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG_TYPE, int(ts->timeSigType()));
815  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::NUMERATOR_STRING, ts->numeratorString());
816  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::DENOMINATOR_STRING, ts->denominatorString());
817  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG_STRETCH, QVariant::fromValue(ts->stretch()));
818  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::GROUPS, QVariant::fromValue(ts->groups()));
819  nsig->setSelected(false);
820  nsig->setDropTarget(0);
821  }
822  }
823  }
824  else {
825  Score* mScore = masterScore();
826  Measure* mf = mScore->tick2measure(tick);
827 
828  //
829  // rewrite all measures up to the next time signature
830  //
831  if (mf == mScore->firstMeasure() && mf->nextMeasure() && (mf->ticks() != mf->timesig())) {
832  // handle upbeat
833  mf->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG_NOMINAL, QVariant::fromValue(ns));
834  Measure* m = mf->nextMeasure();
835  Segment* s = m->findSegment(SegmentType::TimeSig, m->tick());
836  mf = s ? 0 : mf->nextMeasure();
837  }
838  else {
839  if (sigmap()->timesig(seg->tick().ticks()).nominal().identical(ns)) {
840  // no change to global time signature,
841  // but we need to rewrite any staves with local time signatures
842  for (int i = 0; i < nstaves(); ++i) {
843  if (staff(i)->timeSig(tick) && staff(i)->timeSig(tick)->isLocal()) {
844  if (!mScore->rewriteMeasures(mf, ns, i)) {
845  undoStack()->current()->unwind();
846  return;
847  }
848  }
849  }
850  mf = 0;
851  }
852  }
853 
854  // try to rewrite the measures first
855  // we will only add time signatures if this succeeds
856  // this means, however, that the rewrite cannot depend on the time signatures being in place
857  if (mf) {
858  if (!mScore->rewriteMeasures(mf, ns, local ? staffIdx : -1)) {
859  undoStack()->current()->unwind();
860  return;
861  }
862  }
863  // add the time signatures
864  std::map<int, TimeSig*> masterTimeSigs;
865  for (Score* score : scoreList()) {
866  Measure* nfm = score->tick2measure(tick);
867  seg = nfm->undoGetSegment(SegmentType::TimeSig, nfm->tick());
868  std::pair<int, int> staffIdxRange = getStaffIdxRange(score);
869  for (int si = staffIdxRange.first; si < staffIdxRange.second; ++si) {
870  TimeSig* nsig = toTimeSig(seg->element(si * VOICES));
871  if (nsig == 0) {
872  nsig = new TimeSig(*ts);
873  nsig->setScore(score);
874  nsig->setTrack(si * VOICES);
875  nsig->setParent(seg);
876  undoAddElement(nsig);
877  if (score->excerpt()) {
878  const int masterTrack = score->excerpt()->tracks().key(nsig->track());
879  TimeSig* masterTimeSig = masterTimeSigs[masterTrack];
880  if (masterTimeSig)
881  undo(new Link(masterTimeSig, nsig));
882  }
883  }
884  else {
885  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SHOW_COURTESY, ts->showCourtesySig());
886  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG_TYPE, int(ts->timeSigType()));
887  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG, QVariant::fromValue(ts->sig()));
888  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::NUMERATOR_STRING, ts->numeratorString());
889  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::DENOMINATOR_STRING, ts->denominatorString());
890 
891  // HACK do it twice to accommodate undo
892  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG_TYPE, int(ts->timeSigType()));
893  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TIMESIG_STRETCH, QVariant::fromValue(ts->stretch()));
894  nsig->undoChangeProperty(Pid::GROUPS, QVariant::fromValue(ts->groups()));
895  nsig->setSelected(false);
896  nsig->setDropTarget(0); // DEBUG
897  }
898 
899  if (score->isMaster())
900  masterTimeSigs[nsig->track()] = nsig;
901  }
902  }
903  }
904  delete ts;
905  }

907 //---------------------------------------------------------
908 // cmdRemoveTimeSig
909 //---------------------------------------------------------
910 
911 void Score::cmdRemoveTimeSig(TimeSig* ts)
912  {
913  if (ts->isLocal() && excerpts().size() > 0) {
914  MScore::setError(CANNOT_CHANGE_LOCAL_TIMESIG);
915  return;
916  }
917 
918  Measure* m = ts->measure();
919  Segment* s = ts->segment();
920 
921  //
922  // we cannot remove a courtesy time signature
923  //
924  if (m->tick() != s->tick())
925  return;
926  Fraction tick = m->tick();
927 
928  // if we remove all time sigs from segment, segment will be already removed by now
929  // but this would leave us no means of detecting that we have have measures in a local timesig
930  // in cases where we try deleting the local time sig
931  // known bug: this means we do not correctly detect non-empty measures when deleting global timesig change after a local one
932  // see http://musescore.org/en/node/51596
933  // Delete the time sig segment from the root score, we will rewriteMeasures from it
934  // since it contains all the music while the part doesn't
935  Score* rScore = masterScore();
936  Measure* rm = rScore->tick2measure(m->tick());
937  Segment* rs = rm->findSegment(SegmentType::TimeSig, s->tick());
938  if (rs)
939  rScore->undoRemoveElement(rs);
940 
941  Measure* pm = m->prevMeasure();
942  Fraction ns(pm ? pm->timesig() : Fraction(4,4));
943 
944  if (!rScore->rewriteMeasures(rm, ns, -1)) {
945  undoStack()->current()->unwind();
946  }
947  else {
948  m = tick2measure(tick); // old m may have been replaced
949  // hack: fix measure rest durations for staves with local time signatures
950  // if a time signature was deleted to reveal a previous local one,
951  // then rewriteMeasures() got the measure rest durations wrong
952  // (if we fixed it to work for delete, it would fail for add)
953  // so we will fix measure rest durations here
954  // TODO: fix rewriteMeasures() to get this right
955  for (int i = 0; i < nstaves(); ++i) {
956  TimeSig* tsig = staff(i)->timeSig(tick);
957  if (tsig && tsig->isLocal()) {
958  for (Measure* nm = m; nm; nm = nm->nextMeasure()) {
959  // stop when time signature changes
960  if (staff(i)->timeSig(nm->tick()) != tsig)
961  break;
962  // fix measure rest duration
963  ChordRest* cr = nm->findChordRest(nm->tick(), i * VOICES);
964  if (cr && cr->isRest() && cr->durationType() == TDuration::DurationType::V_MEASURE)
965  cr->undoChangeProperty(Pid::DURATION, QVariant::fromValue(nm->stretchedLen(staff(i))));
966  //cr->setTicks(nm->stretchedLen(staff(i)));
967  }
968  }
969  }
970  }
971  }

977 Note* Score::addTiedMidiPitch(int pitch, bool addFlag, Chord* prevChord)
978  {
979  Note* n = addMidiPitch(pitch, addFlag);
980  if (prevChord) {
981  Note* nn = prevChord->findNote(n->pitch());
982  if (nn) {
983  Tie* tie = new Tie(this);
984  tie->setStartNote(nn);
985  tie->setEndNote(n);
986  tie->setTick(tie->startNote()->tick());
987  tie->setTick2(tie->endNote()->tick());
988  tie->setTrack(n->track());
989  n->setTieBack(tie);
990  nn->setTieFor(tie);
991  undoAddElement(tie);
992  }
993  }
994  return n;
995  }

1016 //---------------------------------------------------------
1017 // searchNote
1018 // search for note or rest before or at tick position tick
1019 // in staff
1020 //---------------------------------------------------------
1021 
1022 ChordRest* Score::searchNote(const Fraction& tick, int track) const
1023  {
1024  ChordRest* ipe = 0;
1025  SegmentType st = SegmentType::ChordRest;
1026  for (Segment* segment = firstSegment(st); segment; segment = segment->next1(st)) {
1027  ChordRest* cr = segment->cr(track);
1028  if (!cr)
1029  continue;
1030  if (cr->tick() == tick)
1031  return cr;
1032  if (cr->tick() > tick)
1033  return ipe ? ipe : cr;
1034  ipe = cr;
1035  }
1036  return 0;
1037  }

1039 //---------------------------------------------------------
1040 // regroupNotesAndRests
1041 // * combine consecutive rests into fewer rests of longer duration.
1042 // * combine tied notes/chords into fewer notes of longer duration.
1043 // Only operates on one voice - protects manual layout adjustment, etc.
1044 //---------------------------------------------------------
1045 
1046 void Score::regroupNotesAndRests(const Fraction& startTick, const Fraction& endTick, int track)
1047  {
1048  Segment* inputSegment = _is.segment(); // store this so we can get back to it later.
1049  Segment* seg = tick2segment(startTick, true, SegmentType::ChordRest);
1050  for (Measure* msr = seg->measure(); msr && msr->tick() < endTick; msr = msr->nextMeasure()) {
1051  Fraction maxTick = endTick > msr->endTick() ? msr->endTick() : endTick;
1052  if (!seg || seg->measure() != msr)
1053  seg = msr->first(SegmentType::ChordRest);
1054  for (; seg; seg = seg->next(SegmentType::ChordRest)) {
1055  ChordRest* curr = seg->cr(track);
1056  if (!curr)
1057  continue; // this voice is empty here (CR overlaps with CR in other track)
1058  if (seg->tick() + curr->actualTicks() > maxTick)
1059  break; // outside range
1060  if (curr->isRest() && !(curr->tuplet()) && !(toRest(curr)->isGap())) {
1061  // combine consecutive rests
1062  ChordRest* lastRest = curr;
1063  for (Segment* s = seg->next(SegmentType::ChordRest); s; s = s->next(SegmentType::ChordRest)) {
1064  ChordRest* cr = s->cr(track);
1065  if (!cr)
1066  continue; // this voice is empty here
1067  if (!cr->isRest() || s->tick() + cr->actualTicks() > maxTick || toRest(cr)->isGap())
1068  break; // next element in the same voice is not a rest, or it exceeds the selection, or it is a gap
1069  lastRest = cr;
1070  }
1071  Fraction restTicks = lastRest->tick() + lastRest->ticks() - curr->tick();
1072  seg = setNoteRest(seg, curr->track(), NoteVal(), restTicks, Direction::AUTO, false, true);
1073  }
1074  else if (curr->isChord()) {
1075  // combine tied chords
1076  Chord* chord = toChord(curr);
1077  Chord* lastTiedChord = chord;
1078  for (Chord* next = chord->nextTiedChord(); next && next->tick() + next->ticks() <= maxTick; next = next->nextTiedChord()) {
1079  lastTiedChord = next;
1080  }
1081  if (!lastTiedChord)
1082  lastTiedChord = chord;
1083  Fraction noteTicks = lastTiedChord->tick() + lastTiedChord->ticks() - chord->tick();
1084  if (!(curr->tuplet())) {
1085  // store start/end note for backward/forward ties ending/starting on the group of notes being rewritten
1086  size_t numNotes = chord->notes().size();
1087 #if (!defined (_MSCVER) && !defined (_MSC_VER))
1088  Note* tieBack[numNotes];
1089  Note* tieFor[numNotes];
1090 #else
1091  // MSVC does not support VLA. Replace with std::vector. If profiling determines that the
1092  // heap allocation is slow, an optimization might be used.
1093  std::vector<Note *> tieBack(numNotes);
1094  std::vector<Note *> tieFor(numNotes);
1095 #endif
1096  for (size_t i = 0; i < numNotes; i++) {
1097  Note* n = chord->notes()[i];
1098  Note* nn = lastTiedChord->notes()[i];
1099  if (n->tieBack())
1100  tieBack[i] = n->tieBack()->startNote();
1101  else
1102  tieBack[i] = 0;
1103  if (nn->tieFor())
1104  tieFor[i] = nn->tieFor()->endNote();
1105  else
1106  tieFor[i] = 0;
1107  }
1108  Fraction tick = seg->tick();
1109  int tr = chord->track();
1110  Fraction sd = noteTicks;
1111  Tie* tie = 0;
1112  Segment* segment = seg;
1113  ChordRest* cr = toChordRest(segment->element(tr));
1114  Chord* nchord = toChord(chord->clone());
1115  for (size_t i = 0; i < numNotes; i++) { // strip ties from cloned chord
1116  Note* n = nchord->notes()[i];
1117  n->setTieFor(0);
1118  n->setTieBack(0);
1119  }
1120  Chord* startChord = nchord;
1121  Measure* measure = 0;
1122  bool firstpart = true;
1123  for (;;) {
1124  if (tr % VOICES)
1125  expandVoice(segment, tr);
1126  // the returned gap ends at the measure boundary or at tuplet end
1127  Fraction dd = makeGap(segment, tr, sd, cr->tuplet());
1128  if (dd.isZero())
1129  break;
1130  measure = segment->measure();
1131  std::vector<TDuration> dl;
1132  dl = toRhythmicDurationList(dd, false, segment->rtick(), sigmap()->timesig(tick.ticks()).nominal(), measure, 1);
1133  size_t n = dl.size();
1134  for (size_t i = 0; i < n; ++i) {
1135  const TDuration& d = dl[i];
1136  Chord* nchord2 = toChord(nchord->clone());
1137  if (!firstpart)
1138  nchord2->removeMarkings(true);
1139  nchord2->setDurationType(d);
1140  nchord2->setTicks(d.fraction());
1141  std::vector<Note*> nl1 = nchord->notes();
1142  std::vector<Note*> nl2 = nchord2->notes();
1143  if (!firstpart)
1144  for (size_t j = 0; j < nl1.size(); ++j) {
1145  tie = new Tie(this);
1146  tie->setStartNote(nl1[j]);
1147  tie->setEndNote(nl2[j]);
1148  tie->setTick(tie->startNote()->tick());
1149  tie->setTick2(tie->endNote()->tick());
1150  tie->setTrack(tr);
1151  nl1[j]->setTieFor(tie);
1152  nl2[j]->setTieBack(tie);
1153  }
1154  undoAddCR(nchord2, measure, tick);
1155  segment = nchord2->segment();
1156  tick += nchord2->actualTicks();
1157  nchord = nchord2;
1158  firstpart = false;
1159  }
1160  sd -= dd;
1161  if (sd.isZero())
1162  break;
1163  Segment* nseg = tick2segment(tick, false, SegmentType::ChordRest);
1164  if (nseg == 0)
1165  break;
1166  segment = nseg;
1167  cr = toChordRest(segment->element(tr));
1168  if (cr == 0) {
1169  if (tr % VOICES)
1170  cr = addRest(segment, tr, TDuration(TDuration::DurationType::V_MEASURE), 0);
1171  else
1172  break;
1173  }
1174  }
1175  if (_is.slur()) {
1176  // extend slur
1177  _is.slur()->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SPANNER_TICKS, nchord->tick() - _is.slur()->tick());
1178  for (ScoreElement* e : _is.slur()->linkList()) {
1179  Slur* slur = toSlur(e);
1180  for (ScoreElement* ee : nchord->linkList()) {
1181  Element* e1 = static_cast<Element*>(ee);
1182  if (e1->score() == slur->score() && e1->track() == slur->track2()) {
1183  slur->score()->undo(new ChangeSpannerElements(slur, slur->startElement(), e1));
1184  break;
1185  }
1186  }
1187  }
1188  }
1189  // recreate previously stored pending ties
1190  for (size_t i = 0; i < numNotes; i++) {
1191  Note* n = startChord->notes()[i];
1192  Note* nn = nchord->notes()[i];
1193  if (tieBack[i]) {
1194  tie = new Tie(this);
1195  tie->setStartNote(tieBack[i]);
1196  tie->setEndNote(n);
1197  tie->setTick(tie->startNote()->tick());
1198  tie->setTick2(tie->endNote()->tick());
1199  tie->setTrack(track);
1200  n->setTieBack(tie);
1201  tieBack[i]->setTieFor(tie);
1202  undoAddElement(tie);
1203  }
1204  if (tieFor[i]) {
1205  tie = new Tie(this);
1206  tie->setStartNote(nn);
1207  tie->setEndNote(tieFor[i]);
1208  tie->setTick(tie->startNote()->tick());
1209  tie->setTick2(tie->endNote()->tick());
1210  tie->setTrack(track);
1211  n->setTieFor(tie);
1212  tieFor[i]->setTieBack(tie);
1213  undoAddElement(tie);
1214  }
1215  }
1216  if (tie) // at least one tie was created
1217  connectTies();
1218  }
1219  }
1220  }
1221  }
1222  // now put the input state back where it was before
1223  _is.setSegment(inputSegment);
1224  }

1247 //---------------------------------------------------------
1248 // cmdAddTie
1249 //---------------------------------------------------------
1250 
1251 void Score::cmdAddTie(bool addToChord)
1252  {
1253  const std::vector<Note*> noteList = cmdTieNoteList(selection(), noteEntryMode());
1254 
1255  if (noteList.empty()) {
1256  qDebug("no notes selected");
1257  return;
1258  }
1259 
1260  startCmd();
1261  Chord* lastAddedChord = 0;
1262  for (Note* note : noteList) {
1263  if (note->tieFor()) {
1264  qDebug("cmdAddTie: note %p has already tie? noteFor: %p", note, note->tieFor());
1265  continue;
1266  }
1267 
1268  if (noteEntryMode()) {
1269  ChordRest* cr = nullptr;
1270  Chord* c = note->chord();
1271 
1272  // set cursor at position after note
1273  if (c->isGraceBefore()) {
1274  // tie grace note before to main note
1275  cr = toChord(c->parent());
1276  addToChord = true;
1277  }
1278  else {
1279  _is.setSegment(note->chord()->segment());
1280  _is.moveToNextInputPos();
1281  _is.setLastSegment(_is.segment());
1282 
1283  if (_is.cr() == 0)
1284  expandVoice();
1285  cr = _is.cr();
1286  }
1287  if (cr == 0)
1288  break;
1289 
1290  bool addFlag = lastAddedChord != nullptr;
1291 
1292  // try to re-use existing note or chord
1293  Note* n = nullptr;
1294  if (addToChord && cr->isChord()) {
1295  Chord* chord = toChord(cr);
1296  Note* nn = chord->findNote(note->pitch());
1297  if (nn && nn->tpc() == note->tpc())
1298  n = nn; // re-use note
1299  else
1300  addFlag = true; // re-use chord
1301  }
1302 
1303  // if no note to re-use, create one
1304  NoteVal nval(note->noteVal());
1305  if (!n)
1306  n = addPitch(nval, addFlag);
1307  else
1308  select(n);
1309 
1310  if (n) {
1311  if (!lastAddedChord)
1312  lastAddedChord = n->chord();
1313  // n is not necessarily next note if duration span over measure
1314  Note* nnote = searchTieNote(note);
1315  while (nnote) {
1316  // DEBUG: if duration spans over measure
1317  // this does not set line for intermediate notes
1318  // tpc was set correctly already
1319  //n->setLine(note->line());
1320  //n->setTpc(note->tpc());
1321  Tie* tie = new Tie(this);
1322  tie->setStartNote(note);
1323  tie->setEndNote(nnote);
1324  tie->setTrack(note->track());
1325  tie->setTick(note->chord()->segment()->tick());
1326  tie->setTicks(nnote->chord()->segment()->tick() - note->chord()->segment()->tick());
1327  undoAddElement(tie);
1328  if (!addFlag || nnote->chord()->tick() >= lastAddedChord->tick() || nnote->chord()->isGrace()) {
1329  break;
1330  }
1331  else {
1332  note = nnote;
1333  _is.setLastSegment(_is.segment());
1334  nnote = addPitch(nval, true);
1335  }
1336  }
1337  }
1338  }
1339  else {
1340  Note* note2 = searchTieNote(note);
1341  if (note2) {
1342  Tie* tie = new Tie(this);
1343  tie->setStartNote(note);
1344  tie->setEndNote(note2);
1345  tie->setTrack(note->track());
1346  tie->setTick(note->chord()->segment()->tick());
1347  tie->setTicks(note2->chord()->segment()->tick() - note->chord()->segment()->tick());
1348  undoAddElement(tie);
1349  }
1350  }
1351  }
1352  if (lastAddedChord)
1353  nextInputPos(lastAddedChord, false);
1354  endCmd();
1355  }

1361 void Score::cmdToggleTie()
1362  {
1363  const std::vector<Note*> noteList = cmdTieNoteList(selection(), noteEntryMode());
1364 
1365  if (noteList.empty()) {
1366  qDebug("no notes selected");
1367  return;
1368  }
1369 
1370  bool canAddTies = false;
1371  const size_t notes = noteList.size();
1372  std::vector<Note*> tieNoteList(notes);
1373 
1374  for (size_t i = 0; i < notes; ++i) {
1375  Note* n = noteList[i];
1376  if (n->tieFor()) {
1377  tieNoteList[i] = nullptr;
1378  }
1379  else {
1380  Note* tieNote = searchTieNote(n);
1381  tieNoteList[i] = tieNote;
1382  if (tieNote)
1383  canAddTies = true;
1384  }
1385  }
1386 
1387  startCmd();
1388 
1389  if (canAddTies) {
1390  for (size_t i = 0; i < notes; ++i) {
1391  Note* note2 = tieNoteList[i];
1392  if (note2) {
1393  Note* note = noteList[i];
1394 
1395  Tie* tie = new Tie(this);
1396  tie->setStartNote(note);
1397  tie->setEndNote(note2);
1398  tie->setTrack(note->track());
1399  tie->setTick(note->chord()->segment()->tick());
1400  tie->setTicks(note2->chord()->segment()->tick() - note->chord()->segment()->tick());
1401  undoAddElement(tie);
1402  }
1403  }
1404  }
1405  else {
1406  for (Note* n : noteList) {
1407  Tie* tie = n->tieFor();
1408  if (tie)
1409  undoRemoveElement(tie);
1410  }
1411  }
1412 
1413  endCmd();
1414  }

1421 void Score::cmdAddOttava(OttavaType type)
1422  {
1423  const Selection sel = selection(); // copy selection state before the operation.
1424  // add on each staff if possible
1425  if (sel.isRange() && sel.staffStart() != sel.staffEnd() - 1) {
1426  for (int staffIdx = sel.staffStart() ; staffIdx < sel.staffEnd(); ++staffIdx) {
1427  ChordRest* cr1 = sel.firstChordRest(staffIdx * VOICES);
1428  ChordRest* cr2 = sel.lastChordRest(staffIdx * VOICES);
1429  if (!cr1)
1430  continue;
1431  if (cr2 == 0)
1432  cr2 = cr1;
1433  Ottava* ottava = new Ottava(this);
1434  ottava->setOttavaType(type);
1435  ottava->setTrack(cr1->track());
1436  ottava->setTrack2(cr1->track());
1437  ottava->setTick(cr1->tick());
1438  ottava->setTick2(cr2->tick() + cr2->actualTicks());
1439  undoAddElement(ottava);
1440  }
1441  }
1442  else {
1443  ChordRest* cr1;
1444  ChordRest* cr2;
1445  getSelectedChordRest2(&cr1, &cr2);
1446  if (!cr1)
1447  return;
1448  if (cr2 == 0)
1449  cr2 = cr1;
1450 
1451  Ottava* ottava = new Ottava(this);
1452  ottava->setOttavaType(type);
1453 
1454  ottava->setTrack(cr1->track());
1455  ottava->setTrack2(cr1->track());
1456  ottava->setTick(cr1->tick());
1457  ottava->setTick2(cr2->tick() + cr2->actualTicks());
1458  undoAddElement(ottava);
1459  if (!noteEntryMode())
1460  select(ottava, SelectType::SINGLE, 0);
1461  }
1462  }

1476 //---------------------------------------------------------
1477 // cmdFlip
1478 //---------------------------------------------------------
1479 
1480 void Score::cmdFlip()
1481  {
1482  const QList<Element*>& el = selection().elements();
1483  if (el.empty()) {
1484  MScore::setError(NO_FLIPPABLE_SELECTED);
1485  return;
1486  }
1487 
1488  std::set<const Element*> alreadyFlippedElements;
1489  auto flipOnce = [&alreadyFlippedElements](const Element* element, std::function<void()> flipFunction) -> void {
1490  if (alreadyFlippedElements.count(element) == 0) {
1491  alreadyFlippedElements.insert(element);
1492  flipFunction();
1493  }
1494  };
1495  for (Element* e : el) {
1496  if (e->isNote() || e->isStem() || e->isHook()) {
1497  Chord* chord = nullptr;
1498  if (e->isNote()) {
1499  auto note = toNote(e);
1500  chord = note->chord();
1501  }
1502  else if (e->isStem())
1503  chord = toStem(e)->chord();
1504  else
1505  chord = toHook(e)->chord();
1506 
1507  if (chord->beam()) {
1508  if (!selection().isRange())
1509  e = chord->beam();
1510  else
1511  continue;
1512  }
1513  else {
1514  flipOnce(chord, [chord](){
1515  Direction dir = chord->up() ? Direction::DOWN : Direction::UP;
1516  chord->undoChangeProperty(Pid::STEM_DIRECTION, QVariant::fromValue<Direction>(dir));
1517  });
1518  }
1519  }
1520 
1521  if (e->isBeam()) {
1522  auto beam = toBeam(e);
1523  flipOnce(beam, [beam](){
1524  Direction dir = beam->up() ? Direction::DOWN : Direction::UP;
1525  beam->undoChangeProperty(Pid::STEM_DIRECTION, QVariant::fromValue<Direction>(dir));
1526  });
1527  }
1528  else if (e->isSlurTieSegment()) {
1529  auto slurTieSegment = toSlurTieSegment(e)->slurTie();
1530  flipOnce(slurTieSegment, [slurTieSegment](){
1531  Direction dir = slurTieSegment->up() ? Direction::DOWN : Direction::UP;
1532  slurTieSegment->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SLUR_DIRECTION, QVariant::fromValue<Direction>(dir));
1533  });
1534  }
1535  else if (e->isArticulation()) {
1536  auto articulation = toArticulation(e);
1537  flipOnce(articulation, [articulation](){
1538  ArticulationAnchor articAnchor = articulation->anchor();
1539  switch (articAnchor) {
1540  case ArticulationAnchor::TOP_CHORD:
1541  articAnchor = ArticulationAnchor::BOTTOM_CHORD;
1542  break;
1543  case ArticulationAnchor::BOTTOM_CHORD:
1544  articAnchor = ArticulationAnchor::TOP_CHORD;
1545  break;
1546  case ArticulationAnchor::CHORD:
1547  articAnchor = articulation->up() ? ArticulationAnchor::BOTTOM_CHORD : ArticulationAnchor::TOP_CHORD;
1548  break;
1549  case ArticulationAnchor::TOP_STAFF:
1550  articAnchor = ArticulationAnchor::BOTTOM_STAFF;
1551  break;
1552  case ArticulationAnchor::BOTTOM_STAFF:
1553  articAnchor = ArticulationAnchor::TOP_STAFF;
1554  break;
1555  }
1556  PropertyFlags pf = articulation->propertyFlags(Pid::ARTICULATION_ANCHOR);
1557  if (pf == PropertyFlags::STYLED)
1558  pf = PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED;
1559  articulation->undoChangeProperty(Pid::ARTICULATION_ANCHOR, int(articAnchor), pf);
1560  });
1561  }
1562  else if (e->isTuplet()) {
1563  auto tuplet = toTuplet(e);
1564  flipOnce(tuplet, [tuplet](){
1565  Direction dir = tuplet->isUp() ? Direction::DOWN : Direction::UP;
1566  tuplet->undoChangeProperty(Pid::DIRECTION, QVariant::fromValue<Direction>(dir), PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED);
1567  });
1568  }
1569  else if (e->isNoteDot() && e->parent()->isNote()) {
1570  Note* note = toNote(e->parent());
1571  Direction d = note->dotIsUp() ? Direction::DOWN : Direction::UP;
1572  note->undoChangeProperty(Pid::DOT_POSITION, QVariant::fromValue<Direction>(d));
1573  }
1574  else if (e->isTempoText()
1575  || e->isSystemText()
1576  || e->isJump()
1577  || e->isMarker()
1578  || e->isStaffText()
1579  || e->isSticking()
1580  || e->isFingering()
1581  || e->isDynamic()
1582  || e->isHarmony()
1583  || e->isInstrumentChange()
1584  || e->isRehearsalMark()
1585  || e->isMeasureNumber()
1586  || e->isFretDiagram()
1587  || e->isHairpin()
1588  || e->isHairpinSegment()
1589  || e->isOttavaSegment()
1590  || e->isTextLineSegment()
1591  || e->isPedalSegment()
1592  || e->isLetRingSegment()
1593  || e->isPalmMuteSegment()
1594  || e->isFermata()
1595  || e->isLyrics()
1596  || e->isTrillSegment()
1597  || e->isBreath()) {
1598  e->undoChangeProperty(Pid::AUTOPLACE, true);
1599  // getProperty() delegates call from spannerSegment to Spanner
1600  Placement p = Placement(e->getProperty(Pid::PLACEMENT).toInt());
1601  p = (p == Placement::ABOVE) ? Placement::BELOW : Placement::ABOVE;
1602  // TODO: undoChangeProperty() should probably do this directly
1603  // see https://musescore.org/en/node/281432
1604  Element* ee = e->propertyDelegate(Pid::PLACEMENT);
1605  if (!ee)
1606  ee = e;
1607  PropertyFlags pf = ee->propertyFlags(Pid::PLACEMENT);
1608  if (pf == PropertyFlags::STYLED)
1609  pf = PropertyFlags::UNSTYLED;
1610  qreal oldDefaultY = ee->propertyDefault(Pid::OFFSET).toPointF().y();
1611  ee->undoChangeProperty(Pid::PLACEMENT, int(p), pf);
1612  // flip and rebase user offset to new default now that placement has changed
1613  qreal newDefaultY = ee->propertyDefault(Pid::OFFSET).toPointF().y();
1614  if (ee->isSpanner()) {
1615  Spanner* spanner = toSpanner(ee);
1616  for (SpannerSegment* ss : spanner->spannerSegments()) {
1617  if (!ss->isStyled(Pid::OFFSET)) {
1618  QPointF off = ss->getProperty(Pid::OFFSET).toPointF();
1619  qreal oldY = off.y() - oldDefaultY;
1620  off.ry() = newDefaultY - oldY;
1621  ss->undoChangeProperty(Pid::OFFSET, off);
1622  ss->setOffsetChanged(false);
1623  }
1624  }
1625  }
1626  else if (!ee->isStyled(Pid::OFFSET)) {
1627  QPointF off = ee->getProperty(Pid::OFFSET).toPointF();
1628  qreal oldY = off.y() - oldDefaultY;
1629  off.ry() = newDefaultY - oldY;
1630  ee->undoChangeProperty(Pid::OFFSET, off);
1631  ee->setOffsetChanged(false);
1632  }
1633  }
1634  }
1635  }
1636 
1637 //---------------------------------------------------------
1638 // deleteItem
1639 //---------------------------------------------------------
1640 
1641 void Score::deleteItem(Element* el)
1642  {
1643  if (!el)
1644  return;
1645  // cannot remove generated elements
1646  if (el->generated() && !(el->isBracket() || el->isBarLine() || el->isClef() || el->isMeasureNumber()))
1647  return;
1648 // qDebug("%s", el->name());
1649 
1650  switch (el->type()) {
1651  case ElementType::INSTRUMENT_NAME: {
1652  Part* part = el->part();
1653  InstrumentName* in = toInstrumentName(el);
1654  if (in->instrumentNameType() == InstrumentNameType::LONG)
1655  undo(new ChangeInstrumentLong(Fraction(0,1), part, QList<StaffName>()));
1656  else if (in->instrumentNameType() == InstrumentNameType::SHORT)
1657  undo(new ChangeInstrumentShort(Fraction(0,1), part, QList<StaffName>()));
1658  }
1659  break;
1660 
1661  case ElementType::TIMESIG: {
1662  // timesig might already be removed
1663  TimeSig* ts = toTimeSig(el);
1664  Segment* s = ts->segment();
1665  Measure* m = s->measure();
1666  Segment* ns = m->findSegment(s->segmentType(), s->tick());
1667  if (!ns || (ns->element(ts->track()) != ts)) {
1668  qDebug("deleteItem: not found");
1669  break;
1670  }
1671  cmdRemoveTimeSig(ts);
1672  }
1673  break;
1674 
1675  case ElementType::KEYSIG:
1676  {
1677  KeySig* k = toKeySig(el);
1678  undoRemoveElement(k);
1679  for (int i = 0; i < k->part()->nstaves(); i++) {
1680  Staff* staff = k->part()->staff(i);
1681  KeySigEvent e = staff->keySigEvent(k->tick());
1682  updateInstrumentChangeTranspositions(e, staff, k->tick());
1683  }
1684  }
1685  break;
1686 
1687  case ElementType::NOTE:
1688  {
1689  Chord* chord = toChord(el->parent());
1690  if (chord->notes().size() > 1) {
1691  undoRemoveElement(el);
1692  select(chord->downNote(), SelectType::SINGLE, 0);
1693  break;
1694  }
1695  // else fall through
1696  el = chord;
1697  }
1698  // fall through
1699 
1700  case ElementType::CHORD:
1701  {
1702  Chord* chord = toChord(el);
1703  removeChordRest(chord, false);
1704 
1705  // replace with rest
1706  if (chord->noteType() == NoteType::NORMAL) {
1707  Rest* rest = new Rest(this, chord->durationType());
1708  rest->setDurationType(chord->durationType());
1709  rest->setTicks(chord->ticks());
1710 
1711  rest->setTrack(el->track());
1712  rest->setParent(chord->parent());
1713 
1714  Segment* segment = chord->segment();
1715  undoAddCR(rest, segment->measure(), segment->tick());
1716 
1717  Tuplet* tuplet = chord->tuplet();
1718  if (tuplet) {
1719  QList<ScoreElement*> tl = tuplet->linkList();
1720  for (ScoreElement* e : rest->linkList()) {
1721  DurationElement* de = toDurationElement(e);
1722  for (ScoreElement* ee : qAsConst(tl)) {
1723  Tuplet* t = toTuplet(ee);
1724  if (t->score() == de->score() && t->track() == de->track()) {
1725  de->setTuplet(t);
1726  t->add(de);
1727  break;
1728  }
1729  }
1730  }
1731  }
1732  //select(rest, SelectType::SINGLE, 0);
1733  }
1734  else {
1735  // remove segment if empty
1736  Segment* seg = chord->segment();
1737  if (seg->empty())
1738  undoRemoveElement(seg);
1739  }
1740  }
1741  break;
1742 
1743  case ElementType::REPEAT_MEASURE:
1744  {
1745  RepeatMeasure* rm = toRepeatMeasure(el);
1746  removeChordRest(rm, false);
1747  Rest* rest = new Rest(this);
1748  rest->setDurationType(TDuration::DurationType::V_MEASURE);
1749  rest->setTicks(rm->measure()->stretchedLen(rm->staff()));
1750  rest->setTrack(rm->track());
1751  rest->setParent(rm->parent());
1752  Segment* segment = rm->segment();
1753  undoAddCR(rest, segment->measure(), segment->tick());
1754  }
1755  // fall through
1756 
1757  case ElementType::REST:
1758  //
1759  // only allow for voices != 0
1760  // e.g. voice 0 rests cannot be removed
1761  //
1762  {
1763  Rest* rest = toRest(el);
1764  if (rest->tuplet() && rest->tuplet()->elements().empty())
1765  undoRemoveElement(rest->tuplet());
1766  if ((el->voice() != 0) && !rest->tuplet()) {
1767  rest->undoChangeProperty(Pid::GAP, true);
1768  for (ScoreElement* r : el->linkList()) {
1769  Rest* rr = toRest(r);
1770  if (rr->track() % VOICES)
1771  rr->undoChangeProperty(Pid::GAP, true);
1772  }
1773 
1774  // delete them really when only gap rests are in the actual measure.
1775  Measure* m = toRest(el)->measure();
1776  int track = el->track();
1777  if (m->isOnlyDeletedRests(track)) {
1778  static const SegmentType st { SegmentType::ChordRest };
1779  for (const Segment* s = m->first(st); s; s = s->next(st)) {
1780  Element* del = s->element(track);
1781  if (s->segmentType() != st || !del)
1782  continue;
1783  if (toRest(del)->isGap())
1784  undoRemoveElement(del);
1785  }
1786  checkSpanner(m->tick(), m->endTick());
1787  }
1788  else {
1789  // check if the other rest could be combined
1790  Segment* s = toRest(el)->segment();
1791 
1792  std::vector<Rest*> rests;
1793  // find previous segment with cr in this track
1794  Element* pe = 0;
1795  for (Segment* ps = s->prev(SegmentType::ChordRest); ps; ps = ps->prev(SegmentType::ChordRest)) {
1796  Element* elm = ps->element(track);
1797  if (elm && elm->isRest() && toRest(elm)->isGap()) {
1798  pe = el;
1799  rests.push_back(toRest(elm));
1800  }
1801  else if (elm)
1802  break;
1803  }
1804  // find next segment with cr in this track
1805  Segment* ns;
1806  Element* ne = 0;
1807  for (ns = s->next(SegmentType::ChordRest); ns; ns = ns->next(SegmentType::ChordRest)) {
1808  Element* elm = ns->element(track);
1809  if (elm && elm->isRest() && toRest(elm)->isGap()) {
1810  ne = elm;
1811  rests.push_back(toRest(elm));
1812  }
1813  else if (elm)
1814  break;
1815  }
1816 
1817  Fraction stick = pe ? pe->tick() : s->tick();
1818  Fraction ticks = { 0, 1 };
1819 
1820  if (ne)
1821  ticks = ne->tick() - stick + toRest(ne)->actualTicks();
1822  else if (ns)
1823  ticks = ns->tick() - stick;
1824  else
1825  ticks = m->ticks() + m->tick() - stick;
1826 
1827  if (ticks != m->ticks() && ticks != s->ticks()) {
1828  undoRemoveElement(rest);
1829  for (Rest* r : rests) {
1830  undoRemoveElement(r);
1831  }
1832 
1833  Fraction f = ticks;
1834 
1835  std::vector<TDuration> dList = toDurationList(f, true);
1836  if (dList.empty())
1837  break;
1838 
1839  for (const TDuration& d : dList) {
1840  Rest* rr = new Rest(this);
1841  rr->setTicks(d.fraction());
1842  rr->setDurationType(d);
1843  rr->setTrack(track);
1844  rr->setGap(true);
1845  undoAddCR(rr, m, stick);
1846  }
1847  }
1848  }
1849  // Set input position
1850  // TODO If deleted element is last of a sequence, use prev?
1851  if (noteEntryMode())
1852  score()->move("prev-chord");
1853  }
1854  }
1855  break;
1856 
1857  case ElementType::ACCIDENTAL:
1858  if (el->parent()->isNote())
1859  changeAccidental(toNote(el->parent()), AccidentalType::NONE);
1860  else
1861  undoRemoveElement(el);
1862  break;
1863 
1864  case ElementType::BAR_LINE: {
1865  BarLine* bl = toBarLine(el);
1866  Segment* s = bl->segment();
1867  Measure* m = s->measure();
1868  if (s->isBeginBarLineType() || s->isBarLineType()) {
1869  undoRemoveElement(el);
1870  }
1871  else {
1872  if (bl->barLineType() == BarLineType::START_REPEAT) {
1873  Measure* m2 = m->isMMRest() ? m->mmRestFirst() : m;
1874  for (Score* lscore : score()->scoreList()) {
1875  Measure* lmeasure = lscore->tick2measure(m2->tick());
1876  if (lmeasure)
1877  lmeasure->undoChangeProperty(Pid::REPEAT_START, false);
1878  }
1879  }
1880  else if (bl->barLineType() == BarLineType::END_REPEAT) {
1881  Measure* m2 = m->isMMRest() ? m->mmRestLast() : m;
1882  for (Score* lscore : score()->scoreList()) {
1883  Measure* lmeasure = lscore->tick2measure(m2->tick());
1884  if (lmeasure)
1885  lmeasure->undoChangeProperty(Pid::REPEAT_END, false);
1886  }
1887  }
1888  else {
1889  bl->undoChangeProperty(Pid::BARLINE_TYPE, QVariant::fromValue(BarLineType::NORMAL));
1890  }
1891  }
1892  }
1893  break;
1894 
1895  case ElementType::TUPLET:
1896  cmdDeleteTuplet(toTuplet(el), true);
1897  break;
1898 
1899  case ElementType::MEASURE: {
1900  Measure* m = toMeasure(el);
1901  undoRemoveMeasures(m, m);
1902  undoInsertTime(m->tick(), -(m->endTick() - m->tick()));
1903  }
1904  break;
1905 
1906  case ElementType::BRACKET:
1907  undoRemoveBracket(toBracket(el));
1908  break;
1909 
1910  case ElementType::LAYOUT_BREAK:
1911  {
1912  undoRemoveElement(el);
1913  LayoutBreak* lb = toLayoutBreak(el);
1914  MeasureBase* mb = lb->measure();
1915  Measure* m = mb && mb->isMeasure() ? toMeasure(mb) : nullptr;
1916  if (m && m->isMMRest()) {
1917  // propagate to original measure
1918  m = m->mmRestLast();
1919  for (Element* e : m->el()) {
1920  if (e->isLayoutBreak()) {
1921  undoRemoveElement(e);
1922  break;
1923  }
1924  }
1925  }
1926  }
1927  break;
1928 
1929  case ElementType::CLEF:
1930  {
1931  Clef* clef = toClef(el);
1932  Measure* m = clef->measure();
1933  if (m->isMMRest()) {
1934  // propagate to original measure
1935  m = m->mmRestLast();
1936  Segment* s = m->findSegment(SegmentType::Clef, clef->segment()->tick());
1937  if (s && s->element(clef->track())) {
1938  Clef* c = toClef(s->element(clef->track()));
1939  undoRemoveElement(c);
1940  }
1941  }
1942  else {
1943  if (clef->generated()) {
1944  // find the real clef if this is a cautionary one
1945  if (m && m->prevMeasure()) {
1946  Fraction tick = m->tick();
1947  m = m->prevMeasure();
1948  Segment* s = m->findSegment(SegmentType::Clef, tick);
1949  if (s && s->element(clef->track()))
1950  clef = toClef(s->element(clef->track()));
1951  }
1952  }
1953  undoRemoveElement(clef);
1954  }
1955  }
1956  break;
1957 
1958  case ElementType::MEASURE_NUMBER:
1959  {
1960  Measure* mea = toMeasure(el->parent());
1961  switch (mea->measureNumberMode()) {
1962  // If the user tries to remove an automatically generated measure number,
1963  // we should force the measure not to show any measure number
1964  case MeasureNumberMode::AUTO:
1965  mea->undoChangeProperty(Pid::MEASURE_NUMBER_MODE, static_cast<int>(MeasureNumberMode::HIDE));
1966  break;
1967 
1968  // If the user tries to remove a measure number that he added manually,
1969  // then we should set the MeasureNumberMode to AUTO only if will not show if set to auto.
1970  // If after setting the MeasureNumberMode to AUTO, the measure number still shows,
1971  // We need to force the measure to hide its measure number.
1972  case MeasureNumberMode::SHOW:
1973  if (mea->showsMeasureNumberInAutoMode())
1974  mea->undoChangeProperty(Pid::MEASURE_NUMBER_MODE, static_cast<int>(MeasureNumberMode::HIDE));
1975  else
1976  mea->undoChangeProperty(Pid::MEASURE_NUMBER_MODE, static_cast<int>(MeasureNumberMode::AUTO));
1977  break;
1978  case MeasureNumberMode::HIDE:
1979  break;
1980  }
1981  }
1982  break;
1983  case ElementType::REHEARSAL_MARK:
1984  case ElementType::TEMPO_TEXT:
1985  {
1986  Segment* s = toSegment(el->parent());
1987  Measure* m = s->measure();
1988  if (m->isMMRest()) {
1989  // propagate to original measure/element
1990  m = m->mmRestFirst();
1991  Segment* ns = m->findSegment(SegmentType::ChordRest, s->tick());
1992  for (Element* e : ns->annotations()) {
1993  if (e->type() == el->type() && e->track() == el->track()) {
1994  el = e;
1995  undoRemoveElement(el);
1996  break;
1997  }
1998  }
1999  }
2000  else
2001  undoRemoveElement(el);
2002  }
2003  break;
2004 
2005  case ElementType::OTTAVA_SEGMENT:
2006  case ElementType::HAIRPIN_SEGMENT:
2007  case ElementType::TRILL_SEGMENT:
2008  case ElementType::VIBRATO_SEGMENT:
2009  case ElementType::TEXTLINE_SEGMENT:
2010  case ElementType::VOLTA_SEGMENT:
2011  case ElementType::SLUR_SEGMENT:
2012  case ElementType::TIE_SEGMENT:
2013  case ElementType::LYRICSLINE_SEGMENT:
2014  case ElementType::PEDAL_SEGMENT:
2015  case ElementType::GLISSANDO_SEGMENT:
2016  case ElementType::LET_RING_SEGMENT:
2017  case ElementType::PALM_MUTE_SEGMENT:
2018  {
2019  el = toSpannerSegment(el)->spanner();
2020  undoRemoveElement(el);
2021  }
2022  break;
2023 
2024  case ElementType::STEM_SLASH: // cannot delete this elements
2025  case ElementType::HOOK:
2026  qDebug("cannot remove %s", el->name());
2027  break;
2028 
2029  case ElementType::TEXT:
2030  if ((el->parent() && el->parent()->isTBox()) || el->isTBox())
2031  el->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TEXT, QString());
2032  else
2033  undoRemoveElement(el);
2034  break;
2035 
2036  case ElementType::INSTRUMENT_CHANGE:
2037  {
2038  InstrumentChange* ic = static_cast<InstrumentChange*>(el);
2039  Fraction tickStart = ic->segment()->tick();
2040  Part* part = ic->part();
2041  Interval oldV = part->instrument(tickStart)->transpose();
2042  undoRemoveElement(el);
2043  for (KeySig* keySig : ic->keySigs())
2044  deleteItem(keySig);
2045  for (Clef* clef : ic->clefs())
2046  deleteItem(clef);
2047  if (part->instrument(tickStart)->transpose() != oldV) {
2048  auto i = part->instruments()->upper_bound(tickStart.ticks());
2049  Fraction tickEnd;
2050  if (i == part->instruments()->end())
2051  tickEnd = Fraction(-1, 1);
2052  else
2053  tickEnd = Fraction::fromTicks(i->first);
2054  transpositionChanged(part, oldV, tickStart, tickEnd);
2055  }
2056  }
2057  break;
2058 
2059  case ElementType::MARKER:
2060  {
2061  Measure* m = toMeasure(el->parent());
2062  if (m->isMMRest()) {
2063  // find corresponding marker in underlying measure
2064  bool found = false;
2065  // the marker may be in the first measure...
2066  for (Element* e : m->mmRestFirst()->el()) {
2067  if (e->isMarker() && e->subtype() == el->subtype()) {
2068  undoRemoveElement(e);
2069  found = true;
2070  break;
2071  }
2072  }
2073  if (!found) {
2074  // ...or it may be in the last measure
2075  for (Element* e : m->mmRestLast()->el()) {
2076  if (e->isMarker() && e->subtype() == el->subtype()) {
2077  undoRemoveElement(e);
2078  break;
2079  }
2080  }
2081  }
2082  }
2083  // whether m is an mmrest or not, we still need to remove el
2084  undoRemoveElement(el);
2085  }
2086  break;
2087 
2088  case ElementType::JUMP:
2089  {
2090  Measure* m = toMeasure(el->parent());
2091  if (m->isMMRest()) {
2092  // find corresponding jump in underlying measure
2093  for (Element* e : m->mmRestLast()->el()) {
2094  if (e->isJump() && e->subtype() == el->subtype()) {
2095  undoRemoveElement(e);
2096  break;
2097  }
2098  }
2099  }
2100  // whether m is an mmrest or not, we still need to remove el
2101  undoRemoveElement(el);
2102  }
2103  break;
2104 
2105  default:
2106  undoRemoveElement(el);
2107  break;
2108  }
2109  }

2309 /// Deletes elements in the given range that match the

2315 
2316 ChordRest* Score::deleteRange(Segment* s1, Segment* s2, int track1, int track2, const SelectionFilter& filter)
2317  {
2318  ChordRest* cr = nullptr;
2319 
2320  if (s1) {
2321  // delete content from measures underlying mmrests
2322  if (s1 && s1->measure() && s1->measure()->isMMRest())
2323  s1 = s1->measure()->mmRestFirst()->first();

2325  s2 = s2->measure()->mmRestLast()->last();
2326 
2327  const Fraction stick1 = s1->tick();
2328  const Fraction stick2 = s2 ? s2->tick() : lastMeasure()->endTick();
2329 
2330  Segment* ss1 = s1;
2331  if (!ss1->isChordRestType())
2332  ss1 = ss1->next1(SegmentType::ChordRest);
2333  bool fullMeasure = ss1 && (ss1->measure()->first(SegmentType::ChordRest) == ss1)
2334  && (s2 == 0 || s2->isEndBarLineType());
2335 
2336  Fraction tick2 = s2 ? s2->tick() : Fraction(INT_MAX, 1);
2337 
2338  deleteSpannersFromRange(stick1, stick2, track1, track2, filter);
2339 
2340  for (int track = track1; track < track2; ++track) {
2341  if (!filter.canSelectVoice(track))
2342  continue;
2343  Fraction f;
2344  Fraction tick = Fraction(-1, 1);
2345  Tuplet* tuplet = 0;
2346  for (Segment* s = s1; s && (s->tick() < stick2); s = s->next1()) {
2347  if (s->element(track) && s->isBreathType()) {
2348  deleteItem(s->element(track));
2349  continue;
2350  }
2351  // delete annotations just from this segment and track
2352  deleteAnnotationsFromRange(s, s->next1(), track, track + 1, filter);
2353

2355  if (!e)
2356  continue;
2357  if (!s->isChordRestType()) {

2360  if (s->segmentType() != SegmentType::TimeSig && s->segmentType() != SegmentType::KeySig) {
2361  if (!(e->isBarLine()))

2371  f = offset;
2372  tick = s->measure()->tick();
2373  }
2374  else {

2377  }

2385  cmdDeleteTuplet(t, false);

2389  }
2390  }

2392  Tuplet* t = cr1->tuplet();

2394  // remove complete top level tuplet

2399  f += t->ticks();
2400  tuplet = 0;

2406  tuplet = cr1->tuplet();

2408  f = cr1->ticks();
2409  }
2410  else {
2411  removeChordRest(cr1, true);
2412  f += cr1->ticks();
2413  }
2414  }

2416  if (fullMeasure) {
2417  // handle this as special case to be able to
2418  // fix broken measures:
2419  Staff* staff = Score::staff(track / VOICES);
2420  for (Measure* m = s1->measure(); m; m = m->nextMeasure()) {

2424  if (!cr)
2425  cr = r;
2426  if (s2 && (m == s2->measure()))
2427  break;
2428  }
2429  }
2430  else {
2431  Rest* r = setRest(tick, track, f, false, tuplet);

2444 
2445 void Score::cmdDeleteSelection()
2446  {
2447  ChordRest* cr = 0; // select something after deleting notes
2448 
2449  if (selection().isRange()) {
2450  Segment* s1 = selection().startSegment();
2451  Segment* s2 = selection().endSegment();
2452  const Fraction stick1 = selection().tickStart();
2453  const Fraction stick2 = selection().tickEnd();
2454  cr = deleteRange(s1, s2, staff2track(selection().staffStart()), staff2track(selection().staffEnd()), selectionFilter());
2455  s1 = tick2segment(stick1);
2456  s2 = tick2segment(stick2, true);
2457  if (s1 == 0 || s2 == 0)
2458  deselectAll();
2459  else {
2460  _selection.setStartSegment(s1);
2461  _selection.setEndSegment(s2);
2462  _selection.updateSelectedElements();
2463  }
2464  }
2465  else {
2466  // deleteItem modifies selection().elements() list,
2467  // so we need a local copy:
2468  QList<Element*> el = selection().elements();
2469 
2470  // keep track of linked elements that are deleted implicitly
2471  // so we don't try to delete them twice if they are also in selection
2472  QList<ScoreElement*> deletedElements;
2473  // Similarly, deleting one spanner segment, will delete all of them
2474  // so we don't try to delete them twice if they are also in selection
2475  QList<Spanner*> deletedSpanners;
2476 
2477  for (Element* e : el) {
2478  // these are the linked elements we are about to delete
2479  QList<ScoreElement*> links;
2480  if (e->links())
2481  links = *e->links();
2482 
2483  // find location of element to select after deleting notes
2484  // get tick of element itself if that is valid
2485  // or of spanner or parent if that is more valid
2486  Fraction tick = { -1, 1 };
2487  int track = -1;
2488  if (!cr) {
2489  if (e->isNote())
2490  tick = toNote(e)->chord()->tick();
2491  else if (e->isRest())
2492  tick = toRest(e)->tick();
2493  else if (e->isSpannerSegment())
2494  tick = toSpannerSegment(e)->spanner()->tick();
2495  else if (e->isBreath()) {
2496  // we want the tick of the ChordRest that precedes the breath mark (in the same track)
2497  for (Segment* s = toBreath(e)->segment()->prev(); s; s = s->prev()) {
2498  if (s->isChordRestType() && s->element(e->track())) {
2499  tick = s->tick();
2500  break;
2501  }
2502  }
2503  }
2504  else if (e->parent()
2505  && (e->parent()->isSegment() || e->parent()->isChord() || e->parent()->isNote() || e->parent()->isRest()))
2506  tick = e->parent()->tick();
2507  //else tick < 0
2508  track = e->track();
2509  }
2510 
2511  // delete element if we have not done so already
2512  if (!deletedElements.contains(e)) {
2513  // do not delete two spanner segments from the same spanner
2514  if (e->isSpannerSegment()) {
2515  Spanner* spanner = toSpannerSegment(e)->spanner();
2516  if (deletedSpanners.contains(spanner))
2517  continue;
2518  else {
2519  QList<ScoreElement*> linkedSpanners;
2520  if (spanner->links())
2521  linkedSpanners = *spanner->links();
2522  else
2523  linkedSpanners.append(spanner);
2524  for (ScoreElement* se : qAsConst(linkedSpanners))
2525  deletedSpanners.append(toSpanner(se));
2526  }
2527  }
2528  deleteItem(e);
2529  }
2530 
2531  // find element to select
2532  if (!cr && tick >= Fraction(0,1) && track >= 0)
2533  cr = findCR(tick, track);
2534 
2535  // add these linked elements to list of already-deleted elements
2536  for (ScoreElement* se : qAsConst(links))
2537  deletedElements.append(se);
2538  }
2539 
2540  }
2541 
2542  deselectAll();
2543  // make new selection if appropriate
2544  if (noteEntryMode())
2545  cr = _is.cr();
2546  if (cr) {
2547  if (cr->isChord())
2548  select(toChord(cr)->upNote(), SelectType::SINGLE);
2549  else
2550  select(cr, SelectType::SINGLE);
2551  }
2552  }

2558 void Score::cmdFullMeasureRest()

3225 // checkTimeDelete
3226 //---------------------------------------------------------
3227 
3228 bool Score::checkTimeDelete(Segment* startSegment, Segment* endSegment)
3229  {
3230  Measure* m = startSegment->measure();
3231  Measure* endMeasure;
3232 
3233  if (endSegment)
3234  endMeasure = endSegment->prev() ? endSegment->measure() : endSegment->measure()->prevMeasure();
3235  else
3236  endMeasure = lastMeasure();
3237 
3238  Fraction endTick = endSegment ? endSegment->tick() : endMeasure->endTick();
3239  Fraction tick = startSegment->tick();
3240  Fraction etick = (m == endMeasure ? endTick : m->endTick());
3241  bool canDeleteTime = true;
3242 
3243  while (canDeleteTime) {
3244  for (int track = 0; canDeleteTime && track < _staves.size() * VOICES; ++track) {
3245  if (m->hasVoice(track)) {
3246  Segment* fs = m->first(CR_TYPE);
3247  for (Segment* s = fs; s; s = s->next(CR_TYPE)) {
3248  if (s->element(track)) {
3249  ChordRest* cr = toChordRest(s->element(track));
3250  Tuplet* t = cr->tuplet();
3251  DurationElement* de = t ? toDurationElement(t) : toDurationElement(cr);
3252  Fraction f = de->tick() + de->actualTicks();
3253  Fraction cetick = f;
3254  if (cetick <= tick)
3255  continue;
3256  if (de->tick() >= etick)
3257  break;
3258  if (t && (t->tick() < tick || cetick > etick)) {
3259  canDeleteTime = false;
3260  break;
3261  }
3262  }
3263  }
3264  }
3265  }
3266  if (m == endMeasure)
3267  break;
3268  m = endMeasure;
3269  tick = m->tick();
3270  etick = endTick;
3271  }
3272  if (!canDeleteTime) {
3273  QMessageBox::information(0, "MuseScore",
3274  tr("Please select the complete tuplet and retry the command"),
3275  QMessageBox::Ok, QMessageBox::NoButton);
3276  return false;
3277  }
3278  return true;
3279  }

3300  Element* el = selection().element();
3301  if (!el)

3304  if (el->isNote())
3305  cr = toNote(el)->chord();
3306  else if (el->isChordRest())
3307  cr = toChordRest(el);
3308  else

3310  startSegment = cr->segment();
3311  Fraction endTick = startSegment->tick() + cr->actualTicks();
3312  endSegment = tick2measure(endTick)->findSegment(CR_TYPE, endTick);
3313  }
3314  else {
3315  startSegment = selection().startSegment();
3316  endSegment = selection().endSegment();
3317  }
3318 
3319  if (!checkTimeDelete(startSegment, endSegment))
3320  return;
3321 
3322  MeasureBase* is = startSegment->measure();
3323  if (is->isMeasure() && toMeasure(is)->isMMRest())
3324  is = toMeasure(is)->mmRestFirst();
3325  MeasureBase* ie;
3326 
3327  if (endSegment)
3328  ie = endSegment->prev(SegmentType::ChordRest) ? endSegment->measure() : endSegment->measure()->prev();
3329  else
3330  ie = lastMeasure();
3331

3333 
3334  for (;;) {

3336  Fraction tick = startSegment->tick();
3337  Fraction len;
3338  if (ie == is)
3339  len = endTick - tick;
3340  else
3341  len = is->endTick() - tick;

3343  if (is == ie)

3345  is = is->next();
3346  }
3347  endTick = endSegment ? endSegment->tick() : ie->endTick();
3348  if (ie->endTick() != endTick) {
3349  Fraction len = endTick - ie->tick();

3351  if (is == ie)
3352  break;
3353  ie = ie->prev();
3354  }
3355  deleteMeasures(is, ie);
3356  break;
3357  };
3358 
3359  if (noteEntryMode()) {
3360  Segment* currentSegment = endSegment;
3361  ChordRest* cr = nullptr;
3362  if (!currentSegment && lastMeasureMM()) {
3363  // deleted to end of score - get last cr on current track
3364  currentSegment = lastMeasureMM()->last();
3365  if (currentSegment) {

3367  if (cr)
3368  currentSegment = cr->segment();
3369  }
3370  }
3371  if (!currentSegment) {

3375  }

3381  else

3383  }
3384  else {
3385  // could not find cr to select,
3386  // may be that there is a "hole" in the current track
3387  deselectAll();
3388  }
3389  }
3390  else {
3391  deselectAll();

3399 void Score::timeDelete(Measure* m, Segment* startSegment, const Fraction& f)
3400  {
3401  if (f.isZero())
3402  return;
3403 
3404  const Fraction tick = startSegment->rtick();
3405  const Fraction len = f;
3406  const Fraction etick = tick + len;
3407 
3408  Segment* fs = m->first(CR_TYPE);
3409 
3410  for (int track = 0; track < _staves.size() * VOICES; ++track) {
3411  if (m->hasVoice(track)) {
3412  for (Segment* s = fs; s; s = s->next(CR_TYPE)) {
3413  if (s->element(track)) {
3414  ChordRest* cr = toChordRest(s->element(track));
3415  Fraction cetick = cr->rtick() + cr->actualTicks();
3416 
3417  if (cetick <= tick)
3418  continue;
3419  if (s->rtick() >= etick)
3420  break;
3421 
3422  if (cr->isFullMeasureRest()) {
3423  if (cr->rtick() >= tick) {
3424  // Move full-measure rest from the deleted area
3425  undoRemoveElement(cr);
3426  ChordRest* newCR = toChordRest(cr->clone());
3427  newCR->setTicks(cr->ticks() - f);
3428  undoAddCR(newCR, m, m->tick() + etick);
3429  }
3430  else
3431  cr->undoChangeProperty(Pid::DURATION, cr->ticks() - f);
3432  }
3433  // inside deleted area
3434  else if (s->rtick() >= tick && cetick <= etick) {
3435  // inside
3436  undoRemoveElement(cr);
3437  }
3438  else if (s->rtick() >= tick) {
3439  // running out
3440  Fraction ff = cetick - etick;
3441  undoRemoveElement(cr);
3442  createCRSequence(ff, cr, tick + len);
3443  }
3444  else if (s->rtick() < tick && cetick <= etick) {
3445  // running in
3446  Fraction f1 = tick - s->rtick();
3447  changeCRlen(cr, f1, false);
3448  }
3449  else {
3450  // running in/out
3451  Fraction f1 = cr->ticks() - f;
3452  changeCRlen(cr, f1, false);
3453  }
3454  }
3455  }
3456  }
3457  }
3458  const Fraction abstick = startSegment->tick();
3459  undoInsertTime(abstick, -len);
3460 
3461  std::vector<Segment*> emptySegments;
3462 
3463  for (Score* score : masterScore()->scoreList()) {
3464  Measure* localMeasure = score->tick2measure(abstick);
3465 
3466  undo(new InsertTime(score, abstick, -len));
3467 
3468  Fraction updatedTick = tick;
3469  for (Segment* s = localMeasure->first(CR_TYPE); s; s = s->next()) {
3470  if (s->rtick() < etick || s->rtick() == updatedTick)
3471  continue;
3472 
3473  s->undoChangeProperty(Pid::TICK, updatedTick);
3474  updatedTick += s->ticks();
3475 
3476  if (score->isMaster()) {
3477  if (s->isChordRestType() && !s->hasElements())
3478  emptySegments.push_back(s);
3479  }
3480  }
3481 
3482  undo(new ChangeMeasureLen(localMeasure, localMeasure->ticks() - f));
3483  }
3484 
3485  for (Segment* s : emptySegments) {
3486  if (Segment* ns = s->next(CR_TYPE)) {
3487  // Move annotations from the empty segment.
3488  // TODO: do we need to preserve annotations at all?
3489  // Maybe only some types (Tempo etc.)?
3490  for (Element* a : s->annotations()) {
3491  Element* a1 = a->clone();
3492  a1->setParent(ns);
3493  undoRemoveElement(a);
3494  undoAddElement(a1);
3495  }
3496  }
3497  }
3498  }

3764 //---------------------------------------------------------
3765 // undoPropertyChanged
3766 // return true if an property was actually changed
3767 //---------------------------------------------------------
3768 
3769 bool Score::undoPropertyChanged(Element* e, Pid t, const QVariant& st, PropertyFlags ps)
3770  {
3771  bool changed = false;
3772 
3773  if (propertyLink(t) && e->links()) {
3774  for (ScoreElement* ee : *e->links()) {
3775  if (ee == e) {
3776  if (ee->getProperty(t) != st) {
3777  undoStack()->push1(new ChangeProperty(ee, t, st, ps));
3778  changed = true;
3779  }
3780  }
3781  else {
3782  // property in linked element has not changed yet
3783  // push() calls redo() to change it
3784  if (ee->getProperty(t) != e->getProperty(t)) {
3785  undoStack()->push(new ChangeProperty(ee, t, e->getProperty(t), ps), 0);
3786  changed = true;
3787  }
3788  }
3789  }
3790  }
3791  else {
3792  PropertyFlags po = e->propertyFlags(t);
3793  if ((e->getProperty(t) != st) || (ps != po)) {
3794  e->setPropertyFlags(t, ps);
3795  undoStack()->push1(new ChangeProperty(e, t, st, po));
3796  changed = true;
3797  }
3798  }
3799  return changed;
3800  }

3900

3902  interval.flip();

3904  }

3909  undo(new ChangeKeySig(ks, nkey, ks->showCourtesy()));
3910  }
3911  else {
3912  // do not create empty keysig unless custom or atonal
3913  if (tick.isNotZero() || nkey.key() != Key::C || nkey.custom() || nkey.isAtonal()) {

3917  nks->setKeySigEvent(nkey);

3920  undo(new Link(lks, nks));
3921  else
3922  lks = nks;
3923  }
3924  }

3944  }

3956  }
3957  else
3958  nextTick = -1;
3959  }

4127 static Chord* findLinkedChord(Chord* c, Staff* nstaff)
4128  {
4129  Excerpt* se = c->score()->excerpt();
4130  Excerpt* de = nstaff->score()->excerpt();
4131  int strack = c->track();
4132  int dtrack = nstaff->idx() * VOICES + c->voice();
4133 
4134  if (se)
4135  strack = se->tracks().key(strack);
4136 
4137  if (de) {
4138  QList<int> l = de->tracks().values(strack);
4139  if (l.isEmpty()) {
4140  // simply return the first linked chord whose staff is equal to nstaff
4141  for (ScoreElement* ee : c->linkList()) {
4142  Chord* ch = toChord(ee);
4143  if (ch->staff() == nstaff)
4144  return ch;
4145  }
4146  return 0;
4147  }
4148  for (int i : qAsConst(l)) {
4149  if (nstaff->idx() * VOICES <= i && (nstaff->idx() + 1) * VOICES > i) {
4150  dtrack = i;
4151  break;
4152  }
4153  }
4154  }
4155

4157  Measure* nm = nstaff->score()->tick2measure(s->tick());
4158  Segment* ns = nm->findSegment(s->segmentType(), s->tick());

4166  for (Chord* gc : pc->graceNotes()) {
4167  if (c == gc)
4168  break;
4169  index++;
4170  }
4171  if (index < nc->graceNotes().length())
4172  nc = nc->graceNotes().at(index);
4173  }
4174  return nc;
