4210 void Score::undoExchangeVoice(Measure* measure, int srcVoice, int dstVoice, int srcStaff, int dstStaff)
4211  {
4212  Fraction tick = measure->tick();
4213 
4214  for (int staffIdx = srcStaff; staffIdx < dstStaff; ++staffIdx) {
4215  QSet<Staff*> staffList;
4216  for (Staff* s : staff(staffIdx)->staffList())
4217  staffList.insert(s);
4218 
4219  int srcStaffTrack = staffIdx * VOICES;
4220  int srcTrack = srcStaffTrack + srcVoice;
4221  int dstTrack = srcStaffTrack + dstVoice;
4222  int trackDiff = dstVoice - srcVoice;
4223 
4224  //handle score and complete measures first
4225  undo(new ExchangeVoice(measure, srcTrack, dstTrack, staffIdx));
4226 
4227  for (Staff* st : staffList) {
4228  int staffTrack = st->idx() * VOICES;
4229  Measure* measure2 = st->score()->tick2measure(tick);
4230  Excerpt* ex = st->score()->excerpt();
4231 
4232  if (ex) {
4233  QMultiMap<int, int> tracks = ex->tracks();
4234  QList<int> srcTrackList = tracks.values(srcTrack);
4235  QList<int> dstTrackList = tracks.values(dstTrack);
4236 
4237  for (int srcTrack2 : qAsConst(srcTrackList)) {
4238  // don't care about other linked staves
4239  if (!(staffTrack <= srcTrack2) || !(srcTrack2 < staffTrack + VOICES))
4240  continue;
4241 
4242  int tempTrack = tracks.key(srcTrack2);
4243  QList<int> testTracks = tracks.values(tempTrack + trackDiff);
4244  bool hasVoice = false;
4245  for (int testTrack : qAsConst(testTracks)) {
4246  if (staffTrack <= testTrack && testTrack < staffTrack + VOICES && dstTrackList.contains(testTrack)) {
4247  hasVoice = true;
4248  // voice is simply exchangeable now (deal directly)
4249  undo(new ExchangeVoice(measure2, srcTrack2, testTrack, staffTrack / 4));
4250  }
4251  }
4252 
4253  // only source voice is in this staff
4254  if (!hasVoice) {
4255  undo(new CloneVoice(measure->first(), measure2->endTick(), measure2->first(), tempTrack, srcTrack2, tempTrack + trackDiff));
4256  srcTrackList.removeOne(srcTrack2);
4257  }
4258  }
4259 
4260  for (int dstTrack2 : qAsConst(dstTrackList)) {
4261  // don't care about other linked staves
4262  if (!(staffTrack <= dstTrack2) || !(dstTrack2 < staffTrack + VOICES))
4263  continue;
4264 
4265  int tempTrack = tracks.key(dstTrack2);
4266  QList<int> testTracks = tracks.values(tempTrack - trackDiff);
4267  bool hasVoice = false;
4268  for (int testTrack : qAsConst(testTracks)) {
4269  if (staffTrack <= testTrack && testTrack < staffTrack + VOICES &&
4270  srcTrackList.contains(testTrack))
4271  hasVoice = true;
4272  }
4273 
4274  // only destination voice is in this staff
4275  if (!hasVoice) {
4276  undo(new CloneVoice(measure->first(), measure2->endTick(), measure2->first(), tempTrack, dstTrack2, tempTrack - trackDiff));
4277  dstTrackList.removeOne(dstTrack2);
4278  }
4279  }
4280  }
4281  else if (srcStaffTrack != staffTrack) {
4282  // linked staff in same score (all voices present can be assumed)
4283  undo(new ExchangeVoice(measure2, staffTrack + srcVoice, staffTrack + dstVoice, st->idx()));
4284  }
4285  }
4286  }
4287 
4288  // make sure voice 0 is complete
4289 
4290  if (srcVoice == 0 || dstVoice == 0) {
4291  for (int staffIdx = srcStaff; staffIdx < dstStaff; ++staffIdx) {
4292  // check for complete timeline of voice 0
4293  Fraction ctick = measure->tick();
4294  int track = staffIdx * VOICES;
4295  for (Segment* s = measure->first(SegmentType::ChordRest); s; s = s->next(SegmentType::ChordRest)) {
4296  ChordRest* cr = toChordRest(s->element(track));
4297  if (cr == 0)
4298  continue;
4299  if (cr->isRest()) {
4300  Rest* r = toRest(cr);
4301  if (r->isGap())
4302  r->undoChangeProperty(Pid::GAP, false);
4303  }
4304  if (ctick < s->tick())
4305  setRest(ctick, track, s->tick() - ctick, false, 0); // fill gap
4306  ctick = s->tick() + cr->actualTicks();
4307  }
4308  Fraction etick = measure->endTick();
4309  if (ctick < etick)
4310  setRest(ctick, track, etick - ctick, false, 0); // fill gap
4311  }
4312  }
4313  }

5072  for (auto e : crTuplet->tuplet()->linkList()) {

5115 void Score::undoRemoveElement(Element* element)
5116  {
5117  if (!element)
5118  return;
5119  QList<Segment*> segments;
5120  for (ScoreElement* ee : element->linkList()) {
5121  Element* e = static_cast<Element*>(ee);
5122  undo(new RemoveElement(e));

5126  segments.append(s);
5127  }
5128  if (e->parent() && e->parent()->isSystem()) {
5129  e->setParent(0); // systems will be regenerated upon redo, so detach
5130  }
5131  }

5133  if (s->empty()) {
5134  if (s->header() || s->trailer()) // probably more segment types (system header)
5135  s->setEnabled(false);

5144 //---------------------------------------------------------
5145 
5146 void Score::undoChangeSpannerElements(Spanner* spanner, Element* startElement, Element* endElement)
5147  {
5148  Element* oldStartElement = spanner->startElement();
5149  Element* oldEndElement = spanner->endElement();
5150  int startDeltaTrack = startElement && oldStartElement ? startElement->track() - oldStartElement->track() : 0;
5151  int endDeltaTrack = endElement && oldEndElement ? endElement->track() - oldEndElement->track() : 0;
5152  // scan all spanners linked to this one
5153  for (ScoreElement* el : spanner->linkList()) {
5154  Spanner* sp = toSpanner(el);
5155  Element* newStartElement = nullptr;
5156  Element* newEndElement = nullptr;
5157  // if not the current spanner, but one linked to it, determine its new start and end elements
5158  // as modifications 'parallel' to the modifications of the current spanner's start and end elements
5159  if (sp != spanner) {
5160  if (startElement) {
5161  // determine the track where to expect the 'parallel' start element
5162  int newTrack = sp->startElement() ? sp->startElement()->track() + startDeltaTrack : sp->track();
5163  // look in elements linked to new start element for an element with
5164  // same score as linked spanner and appropriate track
5165  for (ScoreElement* ee : startElement->linkList()) {
5166  Element* e = toElement(ee);
5167  if (e->score() == sp->score() && e->track() == newTrack) {
5168  newStartElement = e;
5169  break;
5170  }
5171  }
5172  }
5173  // similarly to determine the 'parallel' end element
5174  if (endElement) {
5175  int newTrack = sp->endElement() ? sp->endElement()->track() + endDeltaTrack : sp->track2();
5176  for (ScoreElement* ee : endElement->linkList()) {
5177  Element* e = toElement(ee);
5178  if (e->score() == sp->score() && e->track() == newTrack) {
5179  newEndElement = e;
5180  break;
5181  }
5182  }
5183  }
5184  }
5185  // if current spanner, just use stored start and end elements
5186  else {
5187  newStartElement = startElement;
5188  newEndElement = endElement;
5189  }
5190  sp->score()->undo(new ChangeSpannerElements(sp, newStartElement, newEndElement));
5191  }
5192  }

5236 //---------------------------------------------------------
5237 // undoInsertTime
5238 // acts on the linked scores as well
5239 //---------------------------------------------------------
5240 
5241 void Score::undoInsertTime(const Fraction& tick, const Fraction& len)
5242  {
5243  if (len.isZero())
5244  return;
5245 
5246  QList<Spanner*> sl;
5247  for (auto i : _spanner.map()) {
5248  Spanner* s = i.second;
5249  if (s->tick2() < tick)
5250  continue;
5251  bool append = false;
5252  if (len > Fraction(0, 1)) {
5253  if (tick > s->tick() && tick < s->tick2())
5254  append = true;
5255  else if (tick <= s->tick())
5256  append = true;
5257  }
5258  else {
5259  Fraction tick2 = tick - len;
5260  if (s->tick() >= tick2)
5261  append = true;
5262  else if (s->tick() >= tick && s->tick2() <= tick2)
5263  append = true;
5264  else if ((s->tick() <= tick) && (s->tick2() >= tick2)) {
5265  Fraction t2 = s->tick2() + len;
5266  if (t2 > s->tick())
5267  append = true;
5268  }
5269  else if (s->tick() > tick && s->tick2() > tick2)
5270  append = true;
5271  else if (s->tick() < tick && s->tick2() < tick2)
5272  append = true;
5273  }
5274  for (Spanner* ss : sl) {
5275  if (ss->linkList().contains(s)) {
5276  append = false;
5277  break;
5278  }
5279  }
5280  if (append)
5281  sl.append(s);
5282  }
5283  for (Spanner* s : sl) {
5284  if (len > Fraction(0, 1)) {
5285  if (tick > s->tick() && tick < s->tick2()) {
5286  //
5287  // case a:
5288  // +----spanner--------+
5289  // +---add---
5290  //
5291  s->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SPANNER_TICKS, s->ticks() + len);
5292  }
5293  else if (tick <= s->tick()) {
5294  //
5295  // case b:
5296  // +----spanner--------
5297  // +---add---
5298  // and
5299  // +----spanner--------
5300  // +---add---+
5301  Element* startElement = s->startElement();
5302  Element* endElement = s->endElement();
5303  undoChangeSpannerElements(s, nullptr, nullptr);
5304  s->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SPANNER_TICK, s->tick() + len);
5305  undoChangeSpannerElements(s, startElement, endElement);
5306  }
5307  }
5308  else {
5309  Fraction tick2 = tick - len;
5310  if (s->tick() >= tick2) {
5311  //
5312  // case A:
5313  // +----remove---+ +---spanner---+
5314  //
5315  Fraction t = s->tick() + len;
5316  if (t < Fraction(0,1))
5317  t = Fraction(0,1);
5318  Element* startElement = s->startElement();
5319  Element* endElement = s->endElement();
5320  undoChangeSpannerElements(s, nullptr, nullptr);
5321  s->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SPANNER_TICK, t);
5322  undoChangeSpannerElements(s, startElement, endElement);
5323  }
5324  else if (s->tick() >= tick && s->tick2() <= tick2) {
5325  //
5326  // case B:
5327  // +---spanner---+
5328  // +----remove--------+
5329  //
5330  undoRemoveElement(s);
5331  }
5332  else if ((s->tick() <= tick) && (s->tick2() >= tick2)) {
5333  //
5334  // case C:
5335  // +----spanner--------+
5336  // +---remove---+
5337  //
5338  Fraction t2 = s->tick2() + len;
5339  if (t2 > s->tick())
5340  s->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SPANNER_TICKS, s->ticks() + len);
5341  }
5342  else if (s->tick() > tick && s->tick2() > tick2) {
5343  //
5344  // case D:
5345  // +----spanner--------+
5346  // +---remove---+
5347  //
5348  Fraction d1 = s->tick() - tick;
5349  Fraction d2 = tick2 - s->tick();
5350  Fraction le = s->ticks() - d2;
5351  if (le.isZero())
5352  undoRemoveElement(s);
5353  else {
5354  s->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SPANNER_TICK, s->tick() - d1);
5355  s->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SPANNER_TICKS, le);
5356  }
5357  }
5358  else if (s->tick() < tick && s->tick2() < tick2) {
5359  //
5360  // case E:
5361  // +----spanner--------+
5362  // +---remove---+
5363  //
5364  Fraction d = s->tick2() - tick;
5365  Fraction le = s->ticks() - d;
5366  if (le.isZero())
5367  undoRemoveElement(s);
5368  else
5369  s->undoChangeProperty(Pid::SPANNER_TICKS, le);
5370  }
5371  }
5372  }
5373 
5374  undo(new InsertTimeUnmanagedSpanner(this, tick, len));
5375  }

5378 // undoRemoveMeasures
5379 //---------------------------------------------------------
5380 
5381 void Score::undoRemoveMeasures(Measure* m1, Measure* m2, bool preserveTies)
5382  {
5383  Q_ASSERT(m1 && m2);
5384 
5385  const Fraction startTick = m1->tick();
5386  const Fraction endTick = m2->endTick();
5387  std::set<Spanner*> spannersToRemove;
5388 
5389  //
5390  // handle ties which start before m1 and end in (m1-m2)
5391  //
5392  for (Segment* s = m1->first(); s != m2->last(); s = s->next1()) {
5393  if (!s->isChordRestType())
5394  continue;
5395  for (int track = 0; track < ntracks(); ++track) {
5396  Element* e = s->element(track);
5397  if (!e || !e->isChord())
5398  continue;
5399  Chord* c = toChord(e);
5400  for (Note* n : c->notes()) {
5401  // Remove ties crossing measure range boundaries
5402  Tie* t = n->tieBack();
5403  if (t && (t->startNote()->chord()->tick() < startTick)) {
5404  if (preserveTies)
5405  t->setEndNote(0);
5406  else
5407  undoRemoveElement(t);
5408  }
5409  t = n->tieFor();
5410  if (t && (t->endNote()->chord()->tick() >= endTick))
5411  undoRemoveElement(t);
5412 
5413  // Do the same for other note-anchored spanners (e.g. glissandi).
5414  // Delay actual removing to avoid modifying lists inside loops over them.
5415  for (Spanner* sb : n->spannerBack()) {
5416  if (sb->tick() < startTick)
5417  spannersToRemove.insert(sb);
5418  }
5419  for (Spanner* sf : n->spannerFor()) {
5420  if (sf->tick2() >= endTick)
5421  spannersToRemove.insert(sf);
5422  }
5423  }
5424  }
5425  }
5426 
5427  for (Spanner* s : spannersToRemove)
5428  undoRemoveElement(s);
5429 
5430  undo(new RemoveMeasures(m1, m2));
5431  }
